\mt1 Chronicles I 
\c 1  
\p
\v 1  \sc Adam\sc*, Seth, Enosh, 
\v 2 and Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared, 
\v 3 Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, 
\v 4 Noah: the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, Japheth. 
\p
\v 5 The sons of Japheth, Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Elisa, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras. 
\v 6 And the sons of Gomer, Ashkenaz, and Riphath, and Togarmah. 
\v 7 And the sons of Javan, Elishah, and Tarshish, the Kittim, and Rodanim. 
\p
\v 8 And the sons of Ham, Cush, and Mizraim, Put and Canaan. 
\v 9 And the sons of Cush, Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and Sabteca: and the sons of Raamah, Sheba, and Dedan. 
\v 10 And Cush begot Nimrod: he began to be a mighty hunter on the earth. 
\p
\v 17 The sons of Shem, Elam, and Asshur, 
\v 24 and Arpachshad, Shelah, 
\v 25 Eber, Peleg, Reu, 
\v 26 Serug, Nahor, Terah, 
\v 27 Abraham. 
\p
\v 28 And the sons of Abraham, Isaac, and Ishmael. 
\v 29 And these \add are\add* their generations: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth, and Kedar, Abdeel, Mibsam, 
\v 30 Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, 
\v 31 Jetur, Naphish, Kedemah: these \add are\add* the sons of Ishmael. 
\p
\v 32 And the sons of Keturah Abraham’s concubine—and she bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, Shuah: and the sons of Jokshan; Dedan, and Sheba; 
\v 33 and the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Hanoch, and Abida, and Eldaah; all these \add were\add* the sons of Keturah. 
\p
\v 34 And Abraham begot Isaac: and the sons of Isaac \add were\add* Jacob, and Esau. 
\v 35 The sons of Esau, Eliphaz, and Reuel, and Jeush, and Jalam, and Korah. 
\v 36 The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, and Omar, Zepho, and Gatam, and Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek. 
\v 37 And the sons of Reuel, Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. 
\v 38 The sons of Seir, Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. 
\v 39 And the sons of Lotan, Hori, and Hemam; and the sister of Lotan \add was\add* Timna. 
\v 40 The sons of Shobal; Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam: and the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah. 
\v 41 The sons of Anah, Dishon: and the sons of Dishon; Hemdan, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran. 
\v 42 And the sons of Ezer, Bilhan, and Zaavan, and Akan: the sons of Dishan, Uz, and Aran. 
\p
\v 43 And these \add are\add* their kings, Bela the son of Beor; and the name of his city \add was\add* Dinhabah. 
\v 44 And Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead. 
\v 45 And Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead. 
\v 46 And Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad reigned in his stead, who smote Midian in the plain of Moab: and the name of his city \add was\add* Getthaim. 
\v 47 And Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead. 
\v 48 And Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead. 
\v 49 And Shaul died, and Baal-hanan son of Achbor reigned in his stead. 
\v 50 And Baal-hanan died, and Hadad son of Barad reigned in his stead; and the name of his city \add was\add* Pai. 
\p
\v 51 The princes of Edom: prince Timna, prince Alvah, prince Jetheth, 
\v 52 prince Oholibamah, prince Elah, prince Pinon, 
\v 53 prince Kenaz, prince Teman, prince Mibzar, prince Magdiel, 
\v 54 prince Zaphoin. These \add are\add* the princes of Edom. 
\c 2  
\p
\v 1 These \add are\add* the names of the sons of Israel; 
\v 2 Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun, Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, Asher. 
\p
\v 3 The sons of Judah; Er, Onan, Shelah. \add These\add* three were born to him of the daughter of Shua the Canaanitish woman: and Er, the firstborn of Judah, \add was\add* wicked before the Lord, and he slew him. 
\v 4 And Tamar his daughter-in-law bore to him Perez, and Zerah: all the sons of Judah \add were\add* five. 
\p
\v 5 The sons of Perez, Hezron, and Hamul. 
\v 6 And the sons of Zerah, Zimri, and Ethan, and Heman, and Calcol, and Dara, \add in\add* all five. 
\p
\v 7 And the sons of Carmi; Achan the troubler of Israel, who was disobedient in the accursed thing. 
\v 8 And the sons of Ethan; Azariah, 
\v 9 and the sons of Hezron who were born to him; Jerahmeel, and Ram, and Chelubai. 
\p
\v 10 And Ram begot Amminadab, and Amminadab begot Nahshon, chief of the house of Judah. 
\v 11 And Nahshon begot Salmon, and Salmon begot Boaz, 
\v 12 and Boaz begot Obed, and Obed begot Jesse. 
\v 13 And Jesse begot his firstborn Eliab, Abinadab \add was\add* the second, Shimea the third, 
\v 14 Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, 
\v 15 Ozem the sixth, David the seventh. 
\v 16 And their sister \add was\add* Zeruiah, and \add another\add* Abigail: and the sons of Zeruiah \add were\add* Abishai, and Joab, and Asahel, three. 
\v 17 And Abigail bore Amasa: and the father of Amasa \add was\add* Jether the Ishmaelite. 
\p
\v 18 And Caleb the son of Hezron took Azubah to wife, and Jerioth: and these \add were\add* her sons; Jesher, and Shobab, and Ardon. 
\v 19 And Azubah died; and Caleb took to himself Ephrath, and she bore to him Hur. 
\v 20 And Hur begot Uri, and Uri begot Bezalel. 
\v 21 And after this Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, and he took her when he was sixty-five years old; and she bore him Segub. 
\v 22 And Segub begot Jair, and he had twenty-three cities in Gilead. 
\v 23 And he took Geshur and Aram, the towns of Jair from them; \add with\add* Kenath and its towns, sixty cities. All these \add belonged to\add* the sons of Machir the father of Gilead. 
\v 24 And after the death of Hezron, Caleb came to Ephrathah; and the wife of Hezron \add was\add* Abia; and she bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa. 
\p
\v 25 And the sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron \add were\add*, the firstborn Ram, and Bunah, and Oren, and Ozem his brother. 
\v 26 And Jerahmeel had another wife, and her name \add was\add* Atarah: she is the mother of Onam. 
\v 27 And the sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were Maaz, and Jamin, and Eker. 
\v 28 And the sons of Onam were, Shammai, and Jada: and the sons of Shammai; Nadab, and Abishur. 
\v 29 And the name of the wife of Abishur \add was\add* Abihail, and she bore him Ahban, and Molid. 
\v 30 And the sons of Nadab; Seled and Appaim; and Seled died without children. 
\v 31 And the sons of Appaim, Ishi; and the sons of Ishi, Sheshan; and the sons of Sheshan, Dadai. 
\v 32 And the sons of Dadai, Achisamas, Jether, Jonathan: and Jether died childless. 
\v 33 And the sons of Jonathan; Peleth, and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel. 
\p
\v 34 And Sheshan had no sons, but daughters. And Sheshan had an Egyptian servant, and his name \add was\add* Jarha. 
\v 35 And Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant to wife; and she bore him Attai. 
\v 36 And Attai begot Nathan, and Nathan begot Zabad, 
\v 37 and Zabad begot Ephlal, and Ephlal begot Obed. 
\v 38 And Obed begot Jehu, and Jehu begot Azariah, 
\v 39 and Azariah begot Helez, and Helez begot Eleasah, 
\v 40 and Eleasah begot Sismai, and Sismai begot Shallum, 
\v 41 and Shallum begot Jekamiah, and Jekamiah begot Elishama, and Elishama begot Ismael. 
\p
\v 42 And the sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel \add were\add*, Mareshah his firstborn, he \add is\add* the father of Ziph—and the sons of Mareshah the father of Hebron. 
\v 43 And the sons of Hebron; Korah, and Tappuah, and Rekem, and Shema. 
\v 44 And Shema begot Raham the father of Jorkeam: and Jorkeam begot Shammai. 
\v 45 And his son \add was\add* Maon: and Maon \add is\add* the father of Beth-zur. 
\v 46 And Ephah the concubine of Caleb bore Haran, and Moza, and Gazez. 
\v 47 And the sons of Jahdai \add were\add* Regem, and Jotham, and Sogar, and Pelet, and Ephah, and Shaaph. 
\v 48 And Caleb’s concubine Maacah bore Sheber, and Tirhanah. 
\v 49 She bore also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, and Sheva the father of Machbenah, and the father of Gibea: and the daughter of Caleb \add was\add* Achsah. 
\v 50 These were the sons of Caleb. 
\p The sons of Hur the firstborn of Ephrathah; Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim, 
\v 51 Salma the father of Baetha, Lammon the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth-gader. 
\v 52 And the sons of Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim were Haroeh, and Aesi, and Ammanith, 
\v 53 and Umasphae, cities of Jair; Ithrites, and Puthites, and Shumathites, and Mishraites; from these went forth the Zorathites, and the sons of Eshtaol. 
\v 54 The sons of Salma; Bethlehem, the Netophathite, Ataroth of the house of Joab, and half of the family of Manahath, Esari. 
\v 55 The families of the scribes dwelling in Jabez; Tirathites, and Shimeathites, and Sucathites, these \add are\add* the Kenites that came of Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab. 
\c 3  
\p
\v 1 Now these were the sons of David that were born to him in Hebron; the firstborn Amnon, \add born\add* of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess. 
\v 2 The third, Absalom, the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith. 
\v 3 The fifth, Shephatiah, \add the son\add* of Abital; the sixth, Ithream, \add born\add* of Eglah his wife. 
\v 4 Six were born to him in Hebron; and he reigned there seven years and six months: and he reigned thirty-three years in Jerusalem. 
\v 5 And these were born to him in Jerusalem; Shimea, Shobab, Nathan, and Solomon; four \add of\add* Bathsheba the daughter of Ammiel: 
\v 6 and Ibhar, and Elishama, and Eliphelet, 
\v 7 and Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia, 
\v 8 and Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine. 
\v 9 All \add these were\add* the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines, and \add there was also\add* Tamar their sister. 
\p
\v 10 The sons of Solomon; Rehoboam, Abijah his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son, 
\v 11 Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, 
\v 12 Amaziah his son, Uzziah his son, Jotham his son, 
\v 13 Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, 
\v 14 Amon his son, Josiah his son. 
\v 15 And the sons of Josiah; the firstborn Johanan, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum. 
\v 16 And the sons of Jehoiakim; Jechoniah his son, Zedekiah his son. 
\v 17 And the sons of Jechoniah; Asir, Shealtiel his son, 
\v 18 Malchiram, and Pedaiah, and Shenazzar, and Jekamiah, and Hoshama, and Nedabiah. 
\p
\v 19 And the sons of Pedaiah; Zerubbabel, and Shimei: and the sons of Zerubbabel; Meshullam, and Hananiah, and Shelomith \add was\add* their sister. 
\v 20 And Hashubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, and Hasadiah, and Jushab-hesed, five. 
\p
\v 21 And the sons of Hananiah, Pelatiah, and Jeshaiah his son, Rephaiah his son, Arnan his son, Obadiah his son, Shecaniah his son. 
\v 22 And the son of Shecaniah; Shemaiah: and the sons of Shemaiah; Hattush, and Igal, and Bariah and Neariah, and Shaphat, six. 
\p
\v 23 And the sons of Neariah: Elioenai, and Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three. 
\p
\v 24 And the sons of Elioenai; Hodaviah, and Eliashib, and Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Johanan, and Delaiah, and Anani, seven. 
\c 4  
\p
\v 1 And the sons of Judah; Perez, Hezron, and Carmi, and Hur, Shobal, 
\v 2 and Reaiah his son; and Shobal begot Jahath; and Jahath begot Ahumai, and Lahad: these \add are\add* the generations of the Zorathites. 
\v 3 And these \add are\add* the sons of Etam; Jezreel and Ishma, and Idbash: and their sister’s name \add was\add* Hazzelelponi. 
\v 4 And Penuel the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah: these \add are\add* the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem. 
\p
\v 5 And Ashhur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Aoda and Thoada. 
\v 6 And Aoda bore to him Ochaia, and Hepher, and Temeni, and Haahashtari: all these \add were\add* the sons of Aoda. 
\v 7 And the sons of Thoada; Zereth, and Izhar, and Ethnan. 
\v 8 And Koz begot Anub, and Zobebah, and the progeny of the brother of Rechab, the son of Jarin. 
\v 9 And Jabez was more famous than his brethren; and his mother called his name Jabez, saying, I have born as a sorrowful one. 
\v 10 And Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, O that thou wouldest indeed bless me, and enlarge my coasts, and that thy hand might be with me, and that thou wouldest make me know that thou wilt not grieve me! And God granted him all that he asked. 
\p
\v 11 And Chelub the father of Ascha begot Mehir; he \add was\add* the father of Eshton. 
\v 12 He begot Beth-rapha, and Paseah, and Tehinnah the founder of the city of Nahash the brother of Eselom the Kenizzite: these \add were\add* the men of Recah. 
\v 13 And the sons of Kenaz; Othniel, and Seraiah: and the sons of Othniel; Hathath. 
\v 14 And Meonothai begot Ophrah: and Seraiah begot Jobab, the father of Ageaddair, for they were artificers. 
\v 15 And the sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh; Iru, Elah, and Naam: and the sons of Elah, Kenaz. 
\v 16 And the sons of Jehallelel, Ziph, and Ziphah, and Tiria, and Asarel. 
\v 17 And the sons of Esrah; Jether, Mered, and Epher, and Jalon: and Jether begot Miriam, and Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa. 
\v 18 And his wife, that \add is\add* Adia, bore Jered the father of Gedor, and Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah: and these \add are\add* the sons of Betthia the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mored took. 
\v 19 And the sons of the wife of Hodiah the sister of Naham the father of Keilah; Garmi, and Eshtemoa the Maacathite. 
\v 20 And the sons of Shimon; Amnon, and Rinnah the son of Hanan, and Tilon: and the sons of Ishi, Zoheth, and the sons of Zoheth. 
\p
\v 21 The sons of Shelah the son of Judah; Er the father of Lecah, and Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the offspring of the family of Ephrathabac \add belonging to\add* the house of Ashbea. 
\v 22 And Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who dwelt in Moab, and he changed their names to Abederin and Athukiim. 
\v 23 These \add are\add* the potters who dwelt in Netaim and Gederah with the king: they grew strong in his kingdom, and dwelt there. 
\p
\v 24 The sons of Simeon; Nemuel, and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul: 
\v 25 Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son: 
\v 26 Hammuel his son, Sabud his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son. 
\v 27 Shimei \add had\add* sixteen sons, and six daughters; and his brethren had not many sons, neither did all their families multiply as the sons of Judah. 
\v 28 And they dwelt in Beersheba, and Moladah, and in Hazar-shaul, 
\v 29 and in Bilhah, and in Ezem, and in Tolad, 
\v 30 and in Bethuel, and in Hormah, and in Ziklag, 
\v 31 and in Beth-marcaboth, and Hazar-susim, and the house of Biri-shaaraim: these \add were\add* their cities until \add the time of\add* King David. 
\v 32 And their villages \add were\add* Etam, and Ain, Rimmon, and Tochen, and Ashan, five cities. 
\v 33 And all their villages \add were\add* round about these cities, as far as Baal: this \add was\add* their possession, and their distribution. 
\v 34 And Meshobab, and Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah; 
\v 35 and Joel, and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel; 
\v 36 and Elioenai, and Jaakobah, and Jeshohaiah, and Asaiah, and Adiel, and Jesimiel, and Benaiah; 
\v 37 and Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah. 
\v 38 These went by the names of princes in their families, and they increased abundantly in their fathers’ households. 
\p
\v 39 And they went till they came to Gedor, to the east of Gai, to seek pasture for their cattle. 
\v 40 And they found abundant and good pastures, and the land before them \add was\add* wide, and \add there was\add* peace and quietness; for \add there were\add* some of the children of Ham who dwelt there before. 
\v 41 And these who are written by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and they smote the people’s houses, and the Meunites whom they found there, and utterly destroyed them until this day: and they dwelt in their place, because \add there was\add* pasture there for their cattle. 
\v 42 And some of them, \add even\add* of the sons of Simeon, went to Mount Seir, \add even\add* five hundred men; and Pelatiah, and Neariah, and Rephaiah, and Uzziel, sons of Ishi, \add were\add* their rulers. 
\v 43 And they smote the remnant that were left of Amalek, until this day. 
\c 5  
\p
\v 1 And the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for he \add was\add* the firstborn; but because of his going up to his father’s couch, \add his father\add* gave his blessing to his son Joseph, \add even\add* the son of Israel; and he was not reckoned as firstborn; 
\v 2 for Judah \add was\add* very mighty even among his brethren, and one was to be a ruler out of him: but the blessing \add was\add* Joseph’s). 
\v 3 The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel; Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. 
\v 4 The sons of Joel; Shemaiah, and Benaiah his son: and the sons of Gog the son of Shemaiah. 
\v 5 His son \add was\add* Micah, his son Reaiah, his son Baal, 
\v 6 his son Beerah, whom Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria carried away captive: he \add is\add* the chief of the Reubenites. 
\p
\v 7 And his brethren in his family, in their distribution according to their generations; the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah. 
\v 8 And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel: he dwelt in Aroer, and even to Nebo, and Baal-meon. 
\v 9 And he dwelt eastward to the borders of the wilderness, from the river Euphrates: for they had much cattle in the land of Gilead. 
\v 10 And in the days of Saul they made war upon the sojourners \add in the land\add*; and they fell into their hands, all of them dwelling in their tents eastward of Gilead. 
\p
\v 11 The sons of Gad dwelt over against them in the land of Bashan even to Salecah. 
\v 12 Joel the firstborn, and Shapham the second, and Janai the scribe in Bashan. 
\v 13 And their brethren according to the houses of their fathers; Michael, Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jacan, and Zia, and Eber, seven. 
\v 14 These \add are\add* the sons of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Idai, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz, 
\v 15  \add who was\add* the brother of the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, \add he was\add* chief of the house of their families. 
\v 16 They dwelt in Gilead, in Bashan, and in their villages, and \add in\add* all the country round about Sharon to the border. 
\v 17 The enumeration of \add them\add* all took place in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel. 
\p
\v 18 The sons of Reuben and Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, of mighty men, bearing shields and sword, and bending the bow, and skilled in war, \add were\add* forty and four thousand and seven hundred and sixty, going forth to battle. 
\v 19 And they made war with the Hagrites, and Jetur, and Naphish, and Nodab, 
\v 20 and they prevailed against them: and the Hagrites were given into their hands, \add they\add* and all their tents: for they cried to God in the battle, and he hearkened to them, because they trusted on him. 
\v 21 And they took captive their store; five thousand camels, and two hundred and fifty thousand sheep, two thousand asses, and a hundred thousand men. 
\v 22 For many fell slain, because the war \add was\add* of God. And they dwelt in their place until the captivity. 
\p
\v 23 And the half-tribe of Manasseh dwelt from Bashan to Baal-hermon, and Senir, and \add to\add* the Mount Hermon: and they increased in Lebanon. 
\v 24 And these were the heads of the houses of their families; Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valor, men of renown, heads of the houses of their families. 
\p
\v 25 But they rebelled against the God of their fathers, and went a-whoring after the gods of the nations of the land, whom God cast out from before them. 
\v 26 And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, and carried away Reuben and Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and brought them to Halah, and Habor, and to the river Gozan, until this day. 
\p
\v 27 The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. 
\v 28 And the sons of Kohath; Amram, and Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. 
\v 29 And the sons of Amram; Aaron, and Moses, and Miriam: and the sons of Aaron; Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. 
\v 30 Eleazar begot Phinehas, Phinehas begot Abishua; 
\v 31 Abishua begot Bukki, and Bukki begot Uzzi; 
\v 32 Uzzi begot Zerahiah, Zerahiah begot Meraioth; 
\v 33 and Meraioth begot Amariah, and Amariah begot Ahitub; 
\v 34 and Ahitub begot Zadok, and Zadok begot Ahimaaz; 
\v 35 and Ahimaaz begot Azariah, and Azariah begot Johanan; 
\v 36 and Johanan begot Azariah: he ministered as priest in the house which Solomon built in Jerusalem. 
\v 37 And Azariah begot Amariah, and Amariah begot Ahitub; 
\v 38 and Ahitub begot Zadok, and Zadok begot Shallum; 
\v 39 and Shallum begot Hilkiah, and Hilkiah begot Azariah; 
\v 40 and Azariah begot Seraiah, and Seraiah begot Jehozadak. 
\v 41 And Jehozadak went into captivity with Judah and Jerusalem under Nebuchadnezzar. 
\c 6  
\p
\v 1 The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. 
\v 2 And these \add are\add* the names of the sons of Gershom; Libni, and Shimei. 
\v 3 The sons of Kohath; Amram, and Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. 
\v 4 The sons of Merari; Mahli and Mushi: and these \add are\add* the families of Levi, according to their families. 
\v 5 To Gershom—to Libni his son—\add were born\add* Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, 
\v 6 Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son. 
\v 7 The sons of Kohath; Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son; 
\v 8 Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son: 
\v 9 Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, Shaul his son. 
\v 10 And the sons of Elkanah; Amasai, and Ahimoth. 
\v 11 Elkanah his son, Zophai his son, Nahath his son; 
\v 12 Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son. 
\v 13 The sons of Samuel; the firstborn Sani, and Abijah. 
\v 14 The sons of Merari; Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son; 
\v 15 Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son. 
\p
\v 16 And these \add were the men\add* whom David set over the service of the singers in the house of the Lord when the ark was at rest. 
\v 17 And they ministered in front of the tabernacle of witness \add playing\add* on instruments, until Solomon built the house of the Lord in Jerusalem; and they stood according to their order for their services. 
\p
\v 18 And these \add were the men\add* that stood, and their sons, of the sons of Kohath: Heman the psalm singer, son of Joel, the son of Samuel, 
\v 19 the son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of Toah, 
\v 20 the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai, 
\v 21 the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah, 
\v 22 the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, 
\v 23 the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of Israel. 
\v 24 And his brother Asaph, who stood at his right hand; Asaph the son of Berechiah, the son of Shimea, 
\v 25 the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah, 
\v 26 the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, 
\v 27 the son of Adaiah, the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei, 
\v 28 the son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi. 
\v 29 And the sons of Merari their brethren on the left hand: Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch, 
\v 30 the son of Hashabiah, 
\v 31 the son of Amaziah, the son of Bani, the son of Shemer, 
\v 32 the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi. 
\v 33 And their brethren according to the houses of their fathers, \add were\add* the Levites who were appointed to all the work of ministration of the tabernacle of the house of God. 
\p
\v 34 And Aaron and his sons \add were\add* to burn incense on the altar of whole burnt offerings, and on the altar of incense, for all the ministry \add in\add* the holy of holies, and to make atonement for Israel, according to all things that Moses the servant of the Lord commanded. 
\v 35 And these \add are\add* the sons of Aaron; Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua his son, 
\v 36 Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, 
\v 37 Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, 
\v 38 Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son. 
\p
\v 39 And these \add are\add* their residences in their villages, in their coasts, to the sons of Aaron, to their family the Kohathites: for they had the lot. 
\v 40 And they gave them Hebron in the land of Judah, and its suburbs round about it. 
\v 41 But the fields of the city, and its villages, they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh. 
\v 42 And to the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of refuge, \add even\add* Hebron, and Libnah and her suburbs round about, and Hilen and her suburbs, and Eshtemoa and her suburbs, 
\v 43 and Jattir and her suburbs, and Debir and her suburbs, 
\v 44 and Ashan and her suburbs, and Beth-shemesh and her suburbs: 
\v 45 and of the tribe of Benjamin Gibeon and her suburbs, and Alemeth and her suburbs, and Anathoth and her suburbs: all their cities \add were\add* thirteen cities according to their families. 
\p
\v 46 And to the sons of Kohath that were left of their families, \add there were given\add* out of the tribe, \add namely\add*, out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, by lot, ten cities. 
\v 47 And to the sons of Gershom according to their families \add there were given\add* thirteen cities of the tribe of Issachar, of the tribe of Asher, of the tribe of Naphtali, of the tribe of Manasseh in Bashan. 
\v 48 And to the sons of Merari according to their families \add there were given\add*, by lot, twelve cities of the tribe of Reuben, of the tribe of Gad, \add and\add* of the tribe of Zebulun. 
\v 49 So the children of Israel gave to the Levites the cities and their suburbs. 
\v 50 And they gave by lot out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, and out of the tribe of the children of Benjamin, these cities which they call by name. 
\p
\v 51 And \add to the members\add* of the families of the sons of Kohath there were also given the cities of their borders out of the tribe of Ephraim. 
\v 52 And they gave them the cities of refuge, Shechem and her suburbs in Mount Ephraim, and Gezer and her suburbs, 
\v 53 and Jokmeam and her suburbs, and Beth-horon and her suburbs, 
\v 54 and Aijalon and her suburbs, and Gath-rimmon and her suburbs: 
\v 55 and of the half-tribe of Manasseh Aner and her suburbs, and Bileam and her suburbs, to the sons of Kohath that were left, according to \add each several\add* family. 
\p
\v 56 To the sons of Gershom from the families of the half-tribe of Manasseh \add they gave\add* Golan of Bashan and her suburbs, and Ashtaroth and her suburbs. 
\v 57 And out of the tribe of Issachar, Kedesh and her suburbs, and Daberath and her suburbs, and Dabor and her suburbs, 
\v 58 and Ramoth, and Anem and her suburbs. 
\v 59 And of the tribe of Asher; Mashal and her suburbs, and Abdon and her suburbs, 
\v 60 and Hukok and her suburbs, and Rehob and her suburbs. 
\v 61 And of the tribe of Naphtali; Kedesh in Galilee and her suburbs, and Hammon and her suburbs, and Kiriathaim and her suburbs. 
\p
\v 62 To the sons of Merari that were left, \add they gave\add* out of the tribe of Zebulun Rimmono and her suburbs, and Tabor and her suburbs: 
\v 63 out of \add the country\add* beyond Jordan; Jericho westward of Jordan: out of the tribe of Reuben; Bezer in the wilderness and her suburbs, and Jahzah and her suburbs, 
\v 64 and Kedemoth and her suburbs, and Mephaath and her suburbs. 
\v 65 Out of the tribe of Gad; Ramoth-gilead and her suburbs, and Mahanaim and her suburbs, 
\v 66 and Heshbon and her suburbs, and Jazer and her suburbs. 
\c 7  
\p
\v 1 And \add as\add* to the sons of Issachar, \add they were\add* Tola, and Puah, and Jashub, and Shimron, four. 
\v 2 And the sons of Tola; Uzzi, Rephaiah, and Jeriel, and Jahmai, and Ibsam, and Shemuel, chiefs of their fathers’ houses \add belonging to\add* Tola, men of might according to their generations; their number in the days of David \add was\add* twenty and two thousand and six hundred. 
\v 3 And the sons of Uzzi; Izrahiah: and the sons of Izrahiah; Michael, Obadiah, and Joel, and Isshiah, five, all rulers. 
\p
\v 4 And with them, according to their generations, according to the houses of their families, \add were men\add* mighty to set \add armies\add* in array for war, thirty and six thousand, for they had multiplied \add their\add* wives and children. 
\v 5 And their brethren among all the families of Issachar, also mighty men, \add were\add* eighty-seven thousand—\add this was\add* the number of them all. 
\p
\v 6 The sons of Benjamin; Bela, and Becher, and Jediael, three. 
\v 7 And the sons of Bela; Ezbon, and Uzzi, and Uzziel, and Jerimoth, and Iri, five; heads of houses of families, mighty men; and their number \add was\add* twenty and two thousand and thirty-four. 
\v 8 And the sons of Becher; Zemirah, and Joash, and Eliezer, and Elioenai, and Omri, and Jeremoth, and Abijah, and Anathoth, and Alemeth: all these \add were\add* the sons of Becher. 
\v 9 And their number according to their generations (\add they were\add* chiefs of their fathers’ houses, men of might), \add was\add* twenty thousand and two hundred. 
\v 10 And the sons of Jediael; Bilhan: and the sons of Bilhan; Jeush, and Benjamin, and Ehud, and Chenaanah, and Zethan, and Tarshish, and Ahishahar. 
\v 11 All these \add were\add* the sons of Jediael, chiefs of their families, men of might, seventeen thousand and two hundred, going forth to war with might. 
\v 12 And Shuppim, and Huppim, and the sons of Ir, Hushim, whose son \add was\add* Aher. 
\p
\v 13 The sons of Naphtali; Jahziel, Guni, and Jezer, and Shallum, his sons, Bilhah his son. 
\p
\v 14 The sons of Manasseh; Asriel, whom his Syrian concubine bore; and she bore to him also Machir the father of Gilead. 
\v 15 And Machir took a wife for Huppim and Shuppim, and his sister’s name was Maacah; and the name of the second \add son\add* was Zelophehad; and to Zelophehad were born daughters. 
\v 16 And Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and called his name Peresh; and his brother’s name \add was\add* Sheresh; his sons \add were\add* Ulam, and Rakem. 
\v 17 And the sons of Ulam; Bedan. These \add were\add* the sons of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh. 
\v 18 And his sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod, and Abiezer, and Mahlah. 
\v 19 And the sons of Shemida were, Ahian, and Shechem, and Likhi, and Aniam. 
\p
\v 20 And the sons of Ephraim; Shuthelah, and Bered his son, and Tahath his son, Eleadah his son, Tahath his son, 
\v 21 and Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer, and Elead: and the men of Gath who were born in the land slew them, because they went down to take their cattle. 
\v 22 And their father Ephraim mourned many days, and his brethren came to comfort him. 
\v 23 And he went in to his wife, and she conceived, and bore a son, and he called his name Beriah, because, \add said he\add*, He was afflicted in my house. 
\v 24 And his daughter \add was\add* Sheerah, and he was among them that were left, and he built Beth-horon the upper and the lower. And the descendants of Uzzen \add were\add* Sheerah, 
\v 25 and Raphah his son, Resheph and Telah his sons, Tahan his son. 
\v 26 To Ladan his son \add was born his\add* son Ammihud, his son Elishama, \add his\add* son 
\v 27 Nun, \add his\add* son Joshua, \add these were\add* his sons. 
\p
\v 28 And their possession and their dwelling \add were\add* Bethel and her towns, to the east Naaran, westward Gezer and her towns, and Shechem and her towns, as far as Gaza and her towns. 
\v 29 And as far as the borders of the sons of Manasseh, Beth-shean and her towns, Taanach and her towns, Megiddo and her towns, Dor and her towns. In this the children of Joseph the son of Israel dwelt. 
\p
\v 30 The sons of Asher; Imnah, and Ishvah, and Ishvi, and Beriah, and Serah their sister. 
\v 31 And the sons of Beriah; Heber, and Malchiel; he \add was\add* the father of Birzaith. 
\v 32 And Heber begot Japhlet, and Shomer, and Hotham, and Shua their sister. 
\v 33 And the sons of Japhlet; Pasach, and Bimhal, and Ashvath: these \add are\add* the sons of Japhlet. 
\v 34 And the sons of Shemer; Achir, and Rohgah, and Jehubbah, and Aram. 
\v 35 And the sons of Helem his brother; Zophah, and Imna, and Shelesh, and Amal. 
\v 36 The sons of Zophah; Suah, and Harnepher, and Shual, and Beri, and Imrah, 
\v 37 and Bezer, and Hod, and Shamma, and Shilshah, and Ithran, and Beera. 
\v 38 And the sons of Jether, Jephunneh, and Pispa, and Ara. 
\v 39 And the sons of Ulla; Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia. 
\p
\v 40 All these \add were\add* the sons of Asher, all heads of families, choice, mighty men, chief leaders: their number for battle array—their number \add was\add* twenty-six thousand men. 
\c 8  
\p
\v 1 Now Benjamin begot Bela his firstborn, and Ashbel his second \add son\add*, Aharah the third, Nohah the fourth, 
\v 2 and Rapha the fifth. 
\v 3 And the sons of Bela were, Addar, and Gera, and Abihud, 
\v 4 and Abishua, and Naaman, and Ahoah, 
\v 5 and Gera, and Shephuphan, and Huram. 
\v 6 These \add were\add* the sons of Ehud: these are the heads of families to them that dwell in Geba, and they removed them to Manahath: 
\v 7 and Naaman, and Ahijah and Gera, he removed them, and he begot Uzza, and Ahihud. 
\p
\v 8 And Shaharaim begot \add children\add* in the plain of Moab, after that he had sent away Hushim and Baara his wives. 
\p
\v 9 And he begot of his wife Hodesh, Jobab, and Zibia, and Mesha, and Malcam, 
\v 10 and Jeuz, and Sachia, and Mirmah: these \add were\add* heads of families. 
\v 11 And of Hushim he begot Abitub, and Elpaal. 
\v 12 And the sons of Elpaal; Eber, Misham, Shemed: he built Ono, and Lod, and its towns: 
\v 13 and Beriah, and Shema; these \add were\add* heads of families among the dwellers in Aijalon, and they drove out the inhabitants of Gath. 
\v 14 And his brethren \add were\add* Shashak, and Jeremoth, 
\v 15 and Zebadiah, and Arad, and Eder, 
\v 16 and Michael, and Ishpah, and Joha, the sons of Beriah: 
\v 17 and Zebadiah, and Meshullam, and Hizki, and Heber, 
\v 18 and Ishmerai, and Izliah, and Jobab, the sons of Elpaal: 
\v 19 and Jakim, and Zichri, and Zabdi, 
\v 20 and Elienai, and Zillethai, 
\v 21 and Eliel, and Adaiah, and Beraiah, and Shimrath, sons of Shimei: 
\v 22 and Ishpan, and Eber, and Eliel, 
\v 23 and Abdon, and Zichri, and Hanan, 
\v 24 and Hananiah, and Ambri, and Elam, \add and\add* Anthothijah, 
\v 25 and Jathin, and Iphdeiah, and Penuel, the sons of Shashak: 
\v 26 and Shamsherai, and Shehariah, and Athaliah, 
\v 27 and Jaareshiah, and Elijah, and Zichri, son of Jeroham. 
\v 28 These \add were\add* heads of families, chiefs according to their generations: these dwelt in Jerusalem. 
\p
\v 29 And the father of Gibeon dwelt in Gibeon; and his wife’s name was Maacah. 
\v 30 And her firstborn son was Abdon, and Zur, and Kish, and Baal, and Nadab, and Ner, 
\v 31 and Gedor and his brother, and Zecher, and Mikloth. 
\v 32 And Mikloth begot Shimeah: for these dwelt in Jerusalem in the presence of their brethren with their brethren. 
\v 33 And Ner begot Kish, and Kish begot Saul, and Saul begot Jonathan, and Malchi-shua, and Abinadab, and Eshbaal. 
\v 34 And the son of Jonathan \add was\add* Merib-baal; and Merib-baal begot Micah. 
\v 35 And the sons of Micah; Pithon, and Melech, and Tarea, and Ahaz. 
\v 36 And Ahaz begot Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah begot Alemeth, and Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri begot Moza; 
\v 37 and Moza begot Binea: Raphah, \add was\add* his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son. 
\p
\v 38 And Azel \add had\add* six sons, and these \add were\add* their names; Azrikam his firstborn, and Ishmael, and Sheariah, and Obadiah, and Hanan, and Asa: all these \add were\add* the sons of Azel. 
\v 39 And the sons of Eshek his brother; Ulam his firstborn, and Jeush the second, and Eliphelet the third. 
\v 40 And the sons of Ulam were mighty men, bending the bow, and multiplying sons and grandsons, a hundred \add and\add* fifty. All these \add were\add* of the sons of Benjamin. 
\c 9  
\p
\v 1 And \add this is\add* all Israel, \add even\add* their enrollment: and these \add are\add* written down in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah, with the \add names of them\add* that were carried away to Babylon for their transgressions. 
\v 2 And they that dwelt before in their possessions in the cities of Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the appointed ones. 
\p
\v 3 And there dwelt in Jerusalem some of the children of Judah, and of the children of Benjamin, and of the children of Ephraim, and Manasseh. 
\v 4 And Uthai, and the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, son of the sons of Perez, the son of Judah. 
\v 5 And of the Shilonites; Asaiah his firstborn, and his sons. 
\v 6 Of the sons of Zerah; Jeuel, and their brethren, six hundred and ninety. 
\p
\v 7 And of the sons of Benjamin; Sallu, son of Meshullam, son of Hodaviah, son of Hassenuah. 
\v 8 And Ibneiah son of Jeroham, and Elah: these \add are\add* the sons of Uzzi the son of Michri: and Meshullam, son of Shephatiah, son of Reuel, son of Ibnijah; 
\v 9 and their brethren according to their generations, nine hundred and fifty-six, all the men \add were\add* heads of families according to the houses of their fathers. 
\p
\v 10 And of the priests; Jedaiah, and Jehoiarib, and Jachin, 
\v 11 and Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the ruler of the house of God; 
\v 12 and Adaiah son of Jeroham, son of Pashhur, son of Malchijah, and Maasai son of Adiel, son of Jahzerah, son of Meshullam, son of Meshillemith, son of Immer; 
\v 13 and their brethren, chiefs of their families, a thousand seven hundred and sixty, mighty \add men\add* for the work of the ministration of the house of God. 
\p
\v 14 And of the Levites; Shemaiah son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari. 
\v 15 And Bakbakkar, and Heresh, and Galal, and Mattaniah son of Mica, son of Zichri, son of Asaph; 
\v 16 and Obadiah, son of Shemaiah, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun, and Berechiah son of Asa, son of Elkanah—who dwelt in the villages of the Netophathites. 
\v 17 The doorkeepers; Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, and Ahiman, and their brethren; Shallum \add was\add* the chief; 
\v 18 and \add he waited\add* hitherto in the king’s gate eastward: these \add are\add* the gates of the companies of the sons of Levi. 
\v 19 And Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his brethren belonging to the house of his father, the Korahites \add were\add* over the works of the service, keeping the watches of the tabernacle, and their fathers over the camp of the Lord, keeping the entrance. 
\p
\v 20 And Phinehas son of Eleazar was head over them before the Lord, and these \add were\add* with him. 
\v 21 Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah \add was\add* keeper of the door of the tabernacle of witness. 
\v 22 All the chosen porters in the gates \add were\add* two hundred and twelve, these \add were\add* in their courts, \add this was\add* their distribution: these David and Samuel the seer established in their charge. 
\v 23 And these and their sons \add were\add* over the gates in the house of the Lord, and in the house of the tabernacle, to keep watch. 
\v 24 The gates were toward the four winds, eastward, westward, northward, southward. 
\v 25 And their brethren \add were\add* in their courts, to enter in weekly from time to time with these. 
\v 26 For four strong \add men\add* have the charge of the gates; and the Levites were over the chambers, and they keep watch over the treasures of the house of God. 
\v 27 For the charge \add was\add* upon them, and these \add were\add* charged with the keys to open the doors of the temple every morning. 
\p
\v 28 And \add some\add* of them \add were appointed\add* over the vessels of service, that they should carry them in by number, and carry them out by number. 
\v 29 And \add some\add* of them \add were\add* appointed over the furniture, and over all the holy vessels, and over the fine flour, the wine, the oil, the frankincense, and the spices. 
\v 30 And some of the priests were makers of the ointment, and \add appointed to prepare\add* the spices. 
\v 31 And Mattithiah of the Levites (he \add was\add* the firstborn of Shallum the Korahite), \add was set\add* in charge over the sacrifices of meat offering of the pan belonging to the high priest. 
\v 32 And Banaias the Kohathite, from among their brethren, \add was set\add* over the showbread, to prepare it every Sabbath. 
\v 33 And these \add were\add* the singers, heads of families of the Levites, \add to whom were\add* established daily courses, for they were employed in the services day and night. 
\v 34 These \add were\add* the heads of the families of the Levites according to their generations; these chiefs dwelt in Jerusalem. 
\p
\v 35 And Jeiel the father of Gibeon dwelt in Gibeon; and his wife’s name \add was\add* Maacah. 
\v 36 And his firstborn son \add was\add* Abdon, and \add he had\add* Zur, and Kish, and Baal, and Ner, and Nadab, 
\v 37 and Gedor and \add his\add* brother, and Zecher, and Mikloth. 
\v 38 And Mikloth begot Shimeam: and these dwelt in the midst of their brethren in Jerusalem, \add even\add* in the midst of their brethren. 
\p
\v 39 And Ner begot Kish, and Kish begot Saul, and Saul begot Jonathan, and Malchi-shua, and Abinadab, and Eshbaal. 
\v 40 And the son of Jonathan \add was\add* Merib-baal: and Merib-baal begot Micah. 
\v 41 And the sons of Micah \add were\add* Pithon and Melech, and Tahrea. 
\v 42 And Ahaz begot Jarah: and Jarah begot Alemeth, and Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri begot Moza. 
\v 43 And Moza begot Binea, and Rephaiah \add was\add* his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son. 
\v 44 And Azel had six sons, and these \add were\add* their names; Azrikam his firstborn, and Ishmael, and Sheariah, and Obadiah, and Hanan, and Asa: these \add were\add* the sons of Azel. 
\c 10  
\p
\v 1 Now the Philistines warred against Israel; and they fled from before the Philistines, and fell down slain in Mount Gilboa. 
\v 2 And the Philistines pursued after Saul, and after his sons; and the Philistines smote Jonathan, and Abinadab, and Malchi-shua, sons of Saul. 
\v 3 And the battle prevailed against Saul, and the archers hit him with bows and arrows, and they were wounded of the bows. 
\v 4 And Saul said to his armor bearer, Draw thy sword, and pierce me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and mock me. But his armor bearer would not, for he was greatly afraid: so Saul took a sword, and fell upon it. 
\v 5 And his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, and he also fell upon his sword. 
\v 6 So Saul died, and his three sons on that day, and all his family died at the same time. 
\v 7 And all the men of Israel that were in the valley saw that Israel fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, and they left their cities, and fled: and the Philistines came and dwelt in them. 
\p
\v 8 And it came to pass on the next \add day\add* that the Philistines came to strip the slain, and they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. 
\v 9 And they stripped him, and took his head, and his armor, and sent them into the land of the Philistines round about, to proclaim the glad tidings to their idols, and to the people. 
\v 10 And they put their armor in the house of their god, and they put his head in the house of Dagon. 
\p
\v 11 And all the dwellers in Gilead heard of all that the Philistines had done to Saul and to Israel. 
\v 12 And all the mighty men rose up from Gilead, and they took the body of Saul, and the bodies of his sons, and brought them to Jabesh, and buried their bones under the oak in Jabesh, and fasted seven days. 
\v 13 So Saul died for his transgressions, wherein he transgressed against God, against the word of the Lord, forasmuch as he kept \add it\add* not, because Saul inquired of a wizard to seek \add counsel\add*, and Samuel the prophet answered him: 
\v 14 and he sought not the Lord: so he slew him, and turned the kingdom to David the son of Jesse. 
\c 11  
\p
\v 1 And all Israel came to David in Hebron, saying, Behold, we \add are\add* thy bones and thy flesh. 
\v 2 And heretofore when Saul was king, thou wast he that led Israel in and out, and the Lord of Israel said to thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be for a ruler over Israel. 
\v 3 And all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron; and King David made a covenant with them in Hebron before the Lord: and they anointed David to be king over Israel, according to the word of the Lord by Samuel. 
\p
\v 4 And the king and his men went to Jerusalem, this \add is\add* Jebus; and there the Jebusites the inhabitants of the land said to David, 
\v 5 Thou shalt not enter in hither. But he took the stronghold of Zion: this \add is\add* the city of David. 
\v 6 And David said, Whoever first smites the Jebusite, even he shall be chief and captain. And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, and became chief. 
\v 7 And David dwelt in the stronghold; therefore he called it the city of David. 
\v 8 And he fortified the city round about. 
\v 9 And David continued to increase, and the Lord Almighty \add was\add* with him. 
\v 10 And these \add are\add* the chiefs of the mighty men, whom David had, who strengthened \add themselves\add* with him in his kingdom, with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the Lord concerning Israel. 
\p
\v 11 And this \add is\add* the list of the mighty \add men\add* of David; Jashobeam, son of Hachmon, first of the thirty: he drew his sword once against three hundred whom he slew at one time. 
\v 12 And after him Eleazar son of Dodai, the Ahohite: he was among the three mighty men. 
\v 13 He was with David in Pas-dammim, and the Philistines were gathered there to battle, and \add there was\add* a portion of the field full of barley; and the people fled before the Philistines. 
\v 14 And he stood in the midst of the portion, and rescued it, and smote the Philistines; and the Lord wrought a great deliverance. 
\p
\v 15 And three of the thirty chiefs went down to the rock to David, to the cave of Adullam, and the camp of the Philistines \add was\add* in the giants’ valley. 
\v 16 And David \add was\add* then in the hold, and the garrison of the Philistines \add was\add* then in Bethlehem. 
\v 17 And David longed, and said, Who will give me water to drink of the well of Bethlehem, that is in the gate? 
\v 18 And the three broke through the camp of the Philistines, and they drew water out of the well that was in Bethlehem, which was in the gate, and they took it, and came to David: but David would not drink it, and poured it out to the Lord, and said, 
\v 19 God forbid that I should do this thing: shall I drink the blood of these men with their lives? for with \add the peril of\add* their lives they brought it. So he would not drink it. These things did the three mighty \add men\add*. 
\p
\v 20 And Abishai the brother of Joab, he was chief of three: he drew his sword against three hundred slain at one time, and he had a name among the \add second\add* three. 
\v 21 He was more famous than the two \add others\add* of the three, and he was chief \add over\add* them; yet he reached not to the \add first\add* three. 
\p
\v 22 And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was the son of a mighty man: many \add were\add* his acts for Kabzeel: he smote two lionlike men of Moab, and he went down and smote a lion in a pit on a snowy day. 
\v 23 And he smote an Egyptian, a wonderful man five cubits \add high\add*; and in the hand of the Egyptian \add there was\add* a spear like a weavers’ beam; and Benaiah went down to him with a staff, and took the spear out of the Egyptian’s hand, and slew him with his own spear. 
\v 24 These things did Benaiah son of Jehoiada, and his name \add was\add* among the three mighties. 
\v 25 He was distinguished beyond the thirty, yet he reached not to the \add first\add* three: and David set him over his family. 
\p
\v 26 And the mighty \add men\add* of the forces \add were\add*, Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem, 
\v 27 Shammoth the Harodite, Helez the Pelonite, 
\v 28 Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, Abiezer the Anathothite, 
\v 29 Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, 
\v 30 Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite, 
\v 31 Ithai the son of Ribai of the hill of Benjamin, Benaiah the Pirathonite, 
\v 32 Hurai of Nachali Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, 
\v 33 Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, 
\v 34 the son of Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite, 
\v 35 Ahiam the son of Sachar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Thyrophar 
\v 36 the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, 
\v 37 Hezro the Carmelite, Naarai the son of Ezbai, 
\v 38 Joel the son of Nathan, Mibhar son of Hagri, 
\v 39 Zelek the son of Ammoni, Naharai the Beerothite, armor bearer to the son of Zeruiah, 
\v 40 Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, 
\v 41 Uriah the Hittite, Zabad son of Ahlai, 
