\c 12  
\p
\v 1 And these \add are\add* they that came to Ziklag, when he yet kept himself close because of Saul the son of Kish; and these \add were\add* among the mighty, aiding \add him\add* in war, 
\v 2 and \add using\add* the bow with the right hand and with the left, and slingers with stones, and \add shooters\add* with bows. Of the brethren of Saul of Benjamin, 
\v 3 the chief \add was\add* Ahiezer, and Joash son of Shemaah the Gibeathite, and Jeziel and Pelet, sons of Azmaveth, and Beracah, and Jehu of Anathoth, 
\v 4 and Ishmaiah the Gibeonite a mighty man among the thirty, and over the thirty; 
\v 5  \add and\add* Jeremiah, and Jahaziel, and Johanan, and Jozabad of Gederah, 
\v 6 Eluzai and Jerimoth, and Bealiah, and Shemariah, and Shephatiah of Haruphite, 
\v 7 Elkanah, and Isshiah, and Azarel, and Joezer, and Jashobeam, and the Korahites, 
\v 8 and Joelah and Zebadiah, sons of Jeroham, and the \add men\add* of Gedor. 
\p
\v 9 And from Gad these separated themselves to David from the wilderness, strong mighty men of war, bearing shields and spears, and their faces \add were as\add* the face of a lion, and they were nimble as roes upon the mountains in speed. 
\v 10 Ezer the chief, Obadiah the second, Eliab the third, 
\v 11 Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth, 
\v 12 Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh, 
\v 13 Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth, 
\v 14 Jeremiah the tenth, Machbannai the eleventh. 
\v 15 These \add were\add* chiefs of the army of the sons of Gad, the least one commander of a hundred, and the greatest one of a thousand. 
\v 16 These \add are\add* the \add men\add* that crossed over Jordan in the first month, and it had overflowed all its banks; and they drove out all the inhabitants of the valleys, from the east to the west. 
\p
\v 17 And there came \add some\add* of the sons of Benjamin and Judah to the assistance of David. 
\v 18 And David went out to meet them, and said to them, If ye are come peaceably to me, let my heart be at peace with you: but if \add ye are come\add* to betray me to my enemies unfaithfully, the God of your fathers look upon it, and reprove it. 
\v 19 And the Spirit came upon Amasai, a captain of the thirty, and he said, 
\q1 Go, David, son of Jesse, 
\q1 Thou and thy people, 
\q1 Peace, peace be to thee, 
\q1 And peace to thy helpers, 
\q1 For thy God has helped thee. 
\m And David received them, and made them captains of the forces. 
\p
\v 20 And \add some\add* came to David from Manasseh, when the Philistines came against Saul to war: and he helped them not, because the captains of the Philistines took counsel, saying, With the heads of those men will he return to his master Saul. 
\v 21 When David was going to Ziklag, there came to him of Manasseh, Adnah and Jozabad, and Jediael, and Michael, and Jozabad, and Elihu, and Zillethai: \add these\add* are the captains of thousands of Manasseh. 
\v 22 And they fought on the side of David against a troop, for they \add were\add* all men of might; and they were commanders in the army, \add because\add* of \add their\add* might. 
\v 23 For daily men came to David, \add till they amounted\add* to a great force, as the force of God. 
\p
\v 24 And these \add are\add* the names of the commanders of the army, who came to David to Hebron, to turn the kingdom of Saul to him according to the word of the Lord. 
\v 25 The sons of Judah, bearing shields and spears, six thousand and eight hundred mighty in war. 
\v 26 Of the sons of Simeon mighty for battle, seven thousand and a hundred. 
\v 27 Of the sons of Levi, four thousand and six hundred. 
\v 28 And Jehoiada the chief \add of the family\add* of Aaron, and with him three thousand and seven hundred. 
\v 29 And Zadok, a young \add man\add* mighty in strength, and \add there were\add* twenty-two leaders of his father’s house. 
\v 30 And of the sons of Benjamin, the brethren of Saul, three thousand: and still the greater part of them kept the guard of the house of Saul. 
\v 31 And of the sons of Ephraim, twenty thousand and eight hundred mighty men, famous in the houses of their fathers. 
\v 32 And of the half-tribe of Manasseh, eighteen thousand, even \add those\add* who were named by name, to make David king. 
\v 33 And of the sons of Issachar having wisdom with regard to the times, knowing what Israel should do, two hundred; and all their brethren with them. 
\p
\v 34 And of Zebulun they that went out to battle, with all weapons of war, \add were\add* fifty thousand to help David, not weakhanded. 
\v 35 And of Naphtali a thousand captains, and with them \add men\add* with shields and spears, thirty-seven thousand. 
\v 36 And of the Danites \add men\add* ready for war twenty-eight thousand and eight hundred. 
\v 37 And of Asher, they that went out to give aid in war, forty thousand. 
\v 38 And from the country beyond Jordan, from Reuben, and the Gadites, and from the half-tribe of Manasseh, a hundred and twenty thousand, with all weapons of war. 
\p
\v 39 All these \add were\add* men of war, setting \add the army\add* in battle array, with a peaceful mind \add toward him\add*, and they came to Hebron to make David king over all Israel: and the rest of Israel \add were of\add* one mind to make David king. 
\v 40 And they were there three days eating and drinking, for their brethren \add had\add* made preparations. 
\v 41 And their neighbors, as far as Issachar and Zebulun and Naphtali, brought to them upon camels, and asses, and mules, and upon calves, victuals, meal, cakes of figs, raisins, wine, and oil, calves and sheep abundantly: for \add there was\add* joy in Israel. 
\c 13  
\p
\v 1 And David took counsel with the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, \add even with\add* every commander. 
\v 2 And David said to the whole congregation of Israel, If it \add seem\add* good to you, and it should be prospered by the Lord our God, let us send to our brethren that are left in all the land of Israel, and let the priests the Levites who are with them in the cities of their possession \add come\add*, and let them be gathered to us. 
\v 3 And let us bring over to us the ark of our God; for men have not inquired \add at\add* it since the days of Saul. 
\v 4 And all the congregation said that they would do thus; for the saying was right in the eyes of all the people. 
\p
\v 5 So David assembled all Israel, from the borders of Egypt even to the entering in of Hamath, to bring in the ark of God from the city of Jearim. 
\v 6 And David brought it up: and all Israel went up to the city of David, which belonged to Judah, to bring up thence the ark of the Lord God who sits between the cherubim, whose name is called \add on it\add*. 
\v 7 And they set the ark of God on a new wagon \add brought\add* out of the house of Abinadab: and Uzzah and his brethren drove the wagon. 
\p
\v 8 And David and all Israel \add were\add* playing before the Lord with all their might, and \add that\add* together with singers, and with harps, and with lutes, with timbrels, and with cymbals, and with trumpets. 
\v 9 And they came as far as the threshing floor: and Uzzah put forth his hand to hold the ark, because the bullock moved it from \add its place\add*. 
\v 10 And the Lord was very angry with Uzzah, and smote him there, because of his stretching forth his hand upon the ark: and he died there before God. 
\v 11 And David was dispirited, because the Lord \add had\add* made a breach on Uzzah: and he called that place the Breach of Uzzah until this day. 
\v 12 And David feared God that day, saying, How shall I bring the ark of God in to myself? 
\v 13 So David brought not the ark home to himself into the city of David, but he turned it aside into the house of Obed-edom the Gittite. 
\p
\v 14 And the ark of God abode in the house of Obed-edom three months: and God blessed Obed-edom and all that he had. 
\c 14  
\p
\v 1 And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar timbers, and masons, and carpenters, to build a house for him. 
\v 2 And David knew that the Lord \add had\add* designed him to be king over Israel; because his kingdom was highly exalted, on account of his people Israel. 
\p
\v 3 And David took more wives in Jerusalem: and there were born to David more sons and daughters. 
\v 4 And these \add are\add* the names of those that were born, who were \add born\add* to him in Jerusalem; Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, and Solomon, 
\v 5 and Ibhar, and Elishua, and Elpelet, 
\v 6 and Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia, 
\v 7 and Elishama, and Beeliada, and Eliphelet. 
\p
\v 8 And the Philistines heard that David was anointed king over all Israel: and all the Philistines went up to seek David; and David heard \add it\add*, and went out to meet them. 
\v 9 And the Philistines came and assembled together in the giants’ valley. 
\v 10 And David inquired of God, saying, Shall I go up against the Philistines? and wilt thou deliver them into my hand? And the Lord said to him, Go up, and I will deliver them into thy hands. 
\v 11 And he went up to Baal-perazim, and David smote them there; and David said, God has broken through enemies by my hand like a breach of water: therefore he called the name of that place, the Breach of Perazim. 
\v 12 And the Philistines left their gods there; and David gave orders to burn them with fire. 
\p
\v 13 And the Philistines once more assembled themselves in the giants’ valley. 
\v 14 And David inquired of God again; and God said to him, Thou shalt not go after them; turn away from them, and thou shalt come upon them near the pear trees. 
\v 15 And it shall be, when thou shalt hear the sound of their tumult in the tops of the pear trees, then thou shalt go into the battle: for God has gone out before thee to smite the army of the Philistines. 
\v 16 And he did as God commanded him: and he smote the army of the Philistines from Gibeon to Gezer. 
\v 17 And the name of David was \add famous\add* in all the land; and the Lord put the terror of him on all the nations. 
\c 15  
\p
\v 1 And \add David\add* made for himself houses in the city of David, and he prepared a place for the ark of God, and made a tent for it. 
\v 2 Then said David, It is not \add lawful for any\add* to bear the ark of God, but the Levites; for the Lord has chosen them to bear the ark of the Lord, and to minister to him forever. 
\p
\v 3 And David assembled all Israel at Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the Lord to the place which he \add had\add* prepared for it. 
\v 4 And David gathered together the sons of Aaron the Levites. 
\v 5 Of the sons of Kohath; \add there was\add* Uriel the chief, and his brethren, a hundred and twenty. 
\v 6 Of the sons of Merari; Asaiah the chief, and his brethren, two hundred and twenty. 
\v 7 Of the sons of Gershom; Joel the chief, and his brethren, a hundred and thirty. 
\v 8 Of the sons of Elizaphan; Shemaiah the chief, and his brethren, two hundred. 
\v 9 Of the sons of Hebron; Eliel the chief, and his brethren eighty. 
\v 10 Of the sons of Uzziel; Amminadab the chief, and his brethren a hundred and twelve. 
\p
\v 11 And David called Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and the Levites, Uriel, Asaiah, and Joel, and Shemaiah, and Eliel, and Amminadab, 
\v 12 and said to them, Ye \add are\add* the heads of the families of the Levites: sanctify yourselves, you and your brethren, and ye shall carry up the ark of the God of Israel, \add to the place\add* which I have prepared for it. 
\v 13 For because ye were not \add ready\add* at the first, our God made a breach upon us, because we sought him not according to the ordinance. 
\v 14 So the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves, to bring up the ark of the God of Israel. 
\v 15 And the sons of the Levites took the ark of God (as Moses commanded by the word of God according to the Scripture) upon their shoulders with staffs. 
\p
\v 16 And David said to the chiefs of the Levites, Set your brethren the singers with musical instruments, lutes, harps, and cymbals, to sound aloud with a voice of joy. 
\v 17 So the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel; Asaph the son of Berechiah \add was one\add* of his brethren; and Ethan the son of Kushaiah was of the sons of Merari their brethren; 
\v 18 and with them their brethren of the second rank, Zechariah, and Jaaziel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, and Elioel, and Eliab, and Benaiah, and Maaseiah, and Mattithiah, and Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, and Obed-edom, and Jeiel, and Azaziah, the porters. 
\v 19 And the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, with brazen cymbals to make \add a sound\add* to be heard. 
\v 20 Zechariah, and Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, Benaiah, with lutes, on Alamoth. 
\v 21 And Mattithiah, and Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, and Obed-edom, and Jeiel, and Azaziah, with harps of Sheminith, to make a loud noise. 
\p
\v 22 And Chenaniah chief of the Levites \add was\add* master of the bands, because he was skillful. 
\v 23 And Berechiah and Elkanah \add were\add* doorkeepers of the ark. 
\v 24 And Shebaniah, and Joshaphat, and Nethanel, and Amasai, and Zechariah, and Benaiah, and Eliezer, the priests, were sounding with trumpets before the ark of God: and Obed-edom and Jehiah \add were\add* doorkeepers of the ark of God. 
\p
\v 25 So David, and the elders of Israel, and the captains of thousands, went to bring up the ark of the covenant from the house of Obed-edom with gladness. 
\v 26 And it came to pass when God strengthened the Levites bearing the ark of the covenant of the Lord, that they sacrificed seven calves and seven rams. 
\v 27 And David \add was\add* girded with a fine linen robe, and all the Levites \add who were\add* bearing the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and the singers, and Chenaniah the master of the band of singers; also upon David \add there was\add* a robe of fine linen. 
\v 28 And all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the Lord with shouting, and with the sound of a horn, and with trumpets, and with cymbals, playing loudly on lutes and harps. 
\v 29 And the ark of the covenant of the Lord arrived, and came to the city of David; and Michal the daughter of Saul looked down through the window, and saw King David dancing and playing: and she despised him in her heart. 
\c 16  
\p
\v 1 So they brought in the ark of God, and set it in the midst of the tabernacle which David pitched for it; and they offered whole burnt offerings and peace offerings before God. 
\v 2 And David finished offering up whole burnt offerings and peace offerings, and blessed the people in the name of the Lord. 
\v 3 And he divided to every man of Israel (both men and women), to \add every\add* man one baker’s loaf, and a cake. 
\v 4 And he appointed before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, Levites to minister \add and\add* lift up the voice, and to give thanks and praise the Lord God of Israel: 
\v 5 Asaph \add was\add* the chief, and next to him Zechariah, Jeiel, Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, and Benaiah, and Obed-edom: and Jeiel sounding with musical instruments, lutes \add and\add* harps, and Asaph with cymbals: 
\v 6 and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests \add sounding\add* continually with trumpets before the ark of the covenant of God in that day. 
\p
\v 7 Then David first gave orders to praise the Lord by the hand of Asaph and his brethren. 
