\q1 And glory in thy praises. 
\q1
\v 36 Blessed \add be\add* the Lord God of Israel 
\q1 From everlasting and to everlasting: 
\p And all the people shall say, Amen. So they praised the Lord. 
\p
\v 37 And they left there Asaph and his brethren before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, to minister before the ark continually, according to the service of each day: from day to day. 
\v 38 And Obed-edom and his brethren \add were\add* sixty and eight; and Obed-edom the son of Jeduthun, and Hosah, \add were\add* to be doorkeepers. 
\v 39 And \add they appointed\add* Zadok the priest, and his brethren the priests, before the tabernacle of the Lord in the high place in Gibeon, 
\v 40 to offer up whole burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of whole burnt offerings continually morning and evening, and according to all things written in the law of the Lord, which he commanded the children of Israel by Moses the servant of God. 
\v 41 And with him \add were\add* Heman and Jeduthun, and the rest chosen out by name to praise the Lord, for his mercy \add endures\add* forever. 
\v 42 And with them \add there were\add* trumpets and cymbals to sound aloud, and musical instruments for the songs of God: and the sons of Jeduthun \add were\add* at the gate. 
\p
\v 43 And all the people went every one to his home: and David returned to bless his house. 
\c 17  
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass as David dwelt in his house, that David said to Nathan the prophet, Behold, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of the Lord \add is\add* under \add curtains\add* of skins. 
\p
\v 2 And Nathan said to David, Do all that is in thy heart; for God \add is\add* with thee. 
\p
\v 3 And it came to pass in that night, that the word of the Lord came to Nathan, \add saying\add*, 
\v 4 Go and say to David my servant, Thus said the Lord, Thou shalt not build me a house for me to dwell in it. 
\v 5 For I have not dwelt in a house from the day that I brought up Israel until this day, but I have been in a tabernacle and a tent, 
\v 6 in all places through which I have gone with all Israel: did I ever speak to \add any\add* one tribe of Israel whom I commanded to feed my people, saying, \add Why is it\add* that ye have not built me a house of cedar? 
\v 7 And now thus shalt thou say to my servant David, Thus saith the Lord Almighty, I took thee from the sheepfold, from following the flocks, to be a ruler over my people Israel: 
\v 8 and I was with thee in all places whither thou wentest, and I destroyed all thine enemies from before thee, and I made for thee a name according to the name of the great ones that are upon the earth. 
\v 9 And I will appoint a place for my people Israel, and I will plant him, and he shall dwell by himself, and shall no longer be anxious; and the son of iniquity shall no longer afflict him, as at the beginning, 
\v 10 and from the days when I appointed judges over my people Israel. Also I have humbled all thine enemies, and I will increase thee, and the Lord will build thee a house. 
\v 11 And it shall come to pass when thy days shall be fulfilled, and thou shalt sleep with thy fathers, that I will raise up thy seed after thee, which shall be of thy bowels, and I will establish his kingdom. 
\v 12 He shall build me a house, and I will set up his throne forever. 
\v 13 I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son: and my mercy will I not withdraw from him, as I withdrew \add it\add* from them that were before thee. 
\v 14 And I will establish him in my house and in his kingdom forever; and his throne shall be set up forever. 
\p
\v 15 According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so spoke Nathan to David. 
\p
\v 16 And King David came and sat before the Lord, and said, Who am I, O Lord God? and what \add is\add* my house, that thou hast loved me forever? 
\v 17 And these things were little in thy sight, O God: thou hast also spoken concerning the house of thy servant for a long time to come, and thou hast looked upon me as a man looks upon his fellow, and hast exalted me, O Lord God. 
\v 18 What shall David do more toward thee to glorify \add thee\add*? and thou knowest thy servant. 
\v 19 And thou hast wrought all this greatness according to thy heart. 
\v 20 O Lord, there is none like thee, and there is no God beside thee, according to all things which we have heard with our ears. 
\v 21 Neither is there another nation upon the earth \add such\add* as thy people Israel, whereas God led him in the way, to redeem a people for himself, to make for himself a great and glorious name, to cast out nations from before thy people, whom thou redeemedst out of Egypt. 
\v 22 And thou hast appointed thy people Israel as a people to thyself forever; and thou, Lord, didst become a God to them. 
\v 23 And now, Lord, let the word which thou spokest to thy servant, and concerning his house, be confirmed forever, and do thou as thou hast spoken. 
\v 24 And let thy name \add be\add* established and magnified forever, \add men\add* saying, Lord, Lord, Almighty God of Israel: and \add let\add* the house of thy servant David \add be\add* established before thee. 
\v 25 For thou, O Lord my God, hast revealed to the ear of thy servant that thou wilt build him a house; therefore thy servant has found a willingness to pray before thee. 
\v 26 And now, Lord, thou thyself art God, and thou hast spoken these good things concerning thy servant. 
\v 27 And now thou hast begun to bless the house of thy servant, so that it should continue forever before thee: for thou, Lord, hast blessed \add it\add*, and do thou bless \add it\add* forever. 
\c 18  
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass afterward, that David smote the Philistines, and routed them, and took Gath and its villages out of the hand of the Philistines. 
\p
\v 2 And he smote Moab; and the Moabites became servants to David, \add and\add* tributaries. 
\p
\v 3 And David smote Hadadezer king of Zobah of Hamath, as he was going to establish power toward the river Euphrates. 
\v 4 And David took of them a thousand chariots, and seven thousand horsemen, and twenty thousand infantry: and David houghed all the chariot \add horses\add*, but there were reserved of them a hundred chariots. 
\v 5 And the Syrian came from Damascus to help Hadadezer king of Zobah; and David smote of the Syrian \add army\add* twenty and two thousand men. 
\v 6 And David put a garrison in Syria near Damascus; and they became tributary servants to David: and the Lord delivered David wherever he went. 
\v 7 And David took the golden collars that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem. 
\v 8 And David took out of Tibhath, and out of the chief cities of Hadadezer very much brass: of this Solomon made the brazen sea, and the pillars, and the brazen vessels. 
\p
\v 9 And Tou king of Hamath heard that David had smitten the whole force of Hadadezer king of Zobah. 
\v 10 And he sent Hadoram his son to King David to ask how he was, and to congratulate him because he had fought against Hadadezer, and smitten him; for Tou was the enemy of Hadadezer. 
\v 11 And all the golden and silver and brazen vessels, even these King David consecrated to the Lord, with the silver and the gold which he took from all the nations; from Edom, and Moab, and from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines, and from Amalek. 
\p
\v 12 And Abishai son of Zeruiah smote the Edomites in the Valley of Salt, eighteen thousand. 
\v 13 And he put garrisons in the valley; and all the Edomites became David’s servants: and the Lord delivered David wherever he went. 
\p
\v 14 So David reigned over all Israel; and he executed judgment and justice to all his people. 
\v 15 And Joab the son of Zeruiah \add was\add* over the army, and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud \add was\add* recorder. 
\v 16 And Zadok son of Ahitub, and Ahimelech son of Abiathar, \add were\add* the priests; and Shavsha \add was\add* the scribe; 
\v 17 and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada \add was\add* over the Cherethite and the Pelethite, and the sons of David were the chief deputies of the king. 
\c 19  
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass after this, \add that\add* Nahash the king of the children of Ammon died, and Hanun his son reigned in his stead. 
\v 2 And David said, I will act kindly toward Hanun the son of Nahash, as his father acted kindly toward me. And David sent messengers to condole with him on the death of his father. So the servants of David came into the land of the children of Ammon to Hanun, to comfort him. 
\v 3 And the chiefs of the children of Ammon said to Hanun, Is it to honor thy father before thee, that David has sent comforters to thee? Have not his servants come to thee that they might search the city, and to spy out the land? 
\v 4 And Hanun took the servants of David, and shaved them, and cut off the half of their garments as far as their tunic, and sent them away. 
\v 5 And there came men to report to David concerning the men: and he sent to meet them, for they were greatly disgraced: and the king said, Dwell in Jericho until your beards have grown, and return. 
\p
\v 6 And the children of Ammon saw that the people of David were ashamed, and Hanun and the children of Ammon sent a thousand talents of silver to hire for themselves chariots and horsemen out of Syria of Mesopotamia, and out of Syria Maacah, and from Zobah. 
\v 7 And they hired for themselves two and thirty thousand chariots, and the king of Maacah and his people; and they came and encamped before Medeba: and the children of Ammon assembled out of their cities, and came to fight. 
\p
\v 8 And David heard, and sent Joab and all the host of mighty men. 
\v 9 And the children of Ammon came forth, and set themselves in array for battle by the gate of the city: and the kings that were come forth encamped by themselves in the plain. 
\v 10 And Joab saw that they were fronting \add him\add* to fight against him before and behind, and he chose \add some\add* out of all the young men of Israel, and they set themselves in array against the Syrian. 
\v 11 And the rest of the people he gave into the hand of his brother Abishai, and they set themselves in array against the children of Ammon. 
\v 12 And he said, If the Syrian should prevail against me, then shalt thou deliver me: and if the children of Ammon should prevail against thee, then will I deliver thee. 
\v 13 Be of good courage, and let us be strong, for our people, and for the cities of our God: and the Lord shall do what \add is\add* good in his eyes. 
\p
\v 14 So Joab and the people that were with him set themselves in battle array against the Syrians, and they fled from them. 
\v 15 And the children of Ammon saw that the Syrians fled, and they also fled from before Abishai, and from before Joab his brother, and they came to the city: and Joab came to Jerusalem. 
\p
\v 16 And the Syrian saw that Israel had defeated him, and he sent messengers, and they brought out the Syrians from beyond the river; and Shophach the commander-in-chief of the forces of Hadadezer \add was\add* before them. 
\v 17 And it was told David; and he gathered all Israel, and crossed over Jordan, and came upon them, and set the battle in array against them. So David set \add his army\add* in array to fight against the Syrians, and they fought against him. 
\v 18 And the Syrians fled from before Israel; and David slew of the Syrians seven thousand \add riders in\add* chariots, and forty thousand infantry, and he slew Shophach the commander-in-chief of the forces. 
\v 19 And the servants of Hadadezer saw that they were defeated before Israel, and they made peace with David and served him: and the Syrians would not anymore help the children of Ammon. 
\c 20  
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass at the return of the year, at the \add time of the\add* going forth of kings \add to war\add*, that Joab gathered the whole force of the army, and they ravaged the land of the children of Ammon; and he came and besieged Rabbah. But David abode in Jerusalem. And Joab smote Rabbah and destroyed it. 
\v 2 And David took the crown of Molchom their king off his head, and the weight of it was found \add to be\add* a talent of gold, and on it were precious stones; and it was \add placed\add* on the head of David: and he brought out the spoils of the city \add which were\add* very great. 
\v 3 And he brought out the people that were in it, and sawed them asunder with saws, and \add cut them\add* with iron axes, and with harrows: and thus David did to all the children of Ammon. And David and all his people returned to Jerusalem. 
\p
\v 4 And it came to pass afterward that there was again war with the Philistines in Gezer: then Sibbecai the Hushathite smote Sippai of the sons of the giants, and laid him low. 
\p
\v 5 And there \add was\add* war again with the Philistines; and Elhanan the son of Jair smote Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, and the wood of his spear \add was\add* as a weavers’ beam. 
\p
\v 6 And there was again war in Gath, and there was a man of extraordinary size, and his fingers \add and toes were\add* six on each hand and foot, four and twenty; and he was descended from the giants. 
\v 7 And he defied Israel, and Jonathan the son of Shimea the brother of David slew him. 
\v 8 These were born to Rapha in Gath; all four were giants, and they fell by the hand of David, and by the hand of his servants. 
\c 21  
\p
\v 1 And the devil stood up against Israel, and moved David to number Israel. 
\v 2 And King David said to Joab and to the captains of the forces, Go, number Israel from Beersheba even to Dan, and bring me \add the account\add*, and I shall know their number. 
\v 3 And Joab said, May the Lord add to his people, a hundredfold as many as they \add are\add*, and \add let\add* the eyes of my lord the king see \add it\add*: all \add are\add* the servants of my lord. Why does my lord seek this thing? \add do it not\add*, lest it become a sin to Israel. 
\v 4 Nevertheless the king’s word prevailed against Joab; and Joab went out and passed through all Israel, and came to Jerusalem. 
\v 5 And Joab gave the number of the mustering of the people to David: and all Israel was a million and a hundred thousand men that drew sword: and the sons of Judah \add were\add* four hundred and seventy thousand men that drew sword. 
\v 6 But he numbered not Levi and Benjamin among them; for the word of the king was painful to Joab. 
\p
\v 7 And \add there was\add* evil in the sight of the Lord respecting this thing; and he smote Israel. 
\v 8 And David said to God, I have sinned exceedingly, in that I have done this thing: and now, I pray thee, remove the sin of thy servant; for I have been exceedingly foolish. 
\p
\v 9 And the Lord spoke to Gad the seer, saying, 
\v 10 Go and speak to David, saying, Thus saith the Lord, I bring three things upon thee: choose one of them for thyself, and I will do it to thee. 
\v 11 And Gad came to David, and said to him, Thus saith the Lord, Choose for thyself, 
\v 12 either three years of famine, or that thou shouldest flee three months from the face of thine enemies, and the sword of thine enemies \add shall be employed\add* to destroy thee, or that the sword of the Lord and pestilence \add should be\add* three days in the land, and the angel of the Lord \add shall be\add* destroying in all the inheritance of Israel. And now consider what I shall answer to him that sent the message. 
\p
\v 13 And David said to Gad, They are very hard for me, even \add all\add* the three: let me fall now into the hands of the Lord, for his mercies \add are\add* very abundant, and let me not fall by any means into the hands of man. 
\p
\v 14 So the Lord brought pestilence upon Israel: and there fell of Israel seventy thousand men. 
\v 15 And God sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it: and as he was destroying, the Lord saw, and repented for the evil, and said to the angel that was destroying, Let it suffice thee; withhold thy hand. And the angel of the Lord stood by the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. 
\v 16 And David lifted up his eyes, and saw the angel of the Lord, standing between the earth and the heaven, and his sword drawn in his hand, stretched out over Jerusalem: and David and the elders clothed in sackcloth, fell upon their faces. 
\v 17 And David said to God, \add Was it\add* not I \add that\add* gave orders to number the people? and I am the guilty one; I have greatly sinned: but these sheep, what have they done? O Lord God, let thy hand be upon me, and upon my father’s house, and not on thy people for destruction, O Lord! 
\p
\v 18 And the angel of the Lord told Gad to tell David, that he should go up to erect an altar to the Lord, in the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. 
\v 19 And David went up according to the word of Gad, which he spoke in the name of the Lord. 
\v 20 And Ornan turned and saw the king; and he hid himself and his four sons with him. Now Ornan was threshing wheat. 
\v 21 And David came to Ornan; and Ornan came forth from the threshing floor, and did obeisance to David with his face to the ground. 
\v 22 And David said to Ornan, Give me thy place of the threshing floor, and I will build upon it an altar to the Lord: give it me for its worth in money, and the plague shall cease from \add among\add* the people. 
\v 23 And Ornan said to David, Take it to thyself, and let my lord the king do what is right in his eyes: see, I have given the calves for a whole burnt offering, and the plow for wood, and the corn for a meat offering; I have given all. 
\v 24 And King David said to Ornan, Nay; for I will surely buy it for its worth in money: for I will not take thy property for the Lord, to offer a whole burnt offering to the Lord without cost \add to myself\add*. 
\v 25 And David gave to Ornan for his place six hundred shekels of gold \add by\add* weight. 
\v 26 And David built there an altar to the Lord, and offered up whole burnt offerings and peace offerings: and he cried to the Lord, and he answered him by fire out of heaven on the altar of whole burnt offerings, and \add it\add* consumed the whole burnt offering. 
\v 27 And the Lord spoke to the angel; and he put up the sword into its sheath. 
\p
\v 28 At that time when David saw that the Lord answered him in the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he also sacrificed there. 
\v 29 And the tabernacle of the Lord which Moses made in the wilderness, and the altar of whole burnt offerings, \add were\add* at that time in the high place at Gibeon. 
\v 30 And David could not go before it to inquire of God; for he hastened not because of the sword of the angel of the Lord. 
\c 22  
\p
\v 1 And David said, This is the house of the Lord God, and this \add is\add* the altar for whole burnt offering for Israel. 
\p
\v 2 And David gave orders to gather all the strangers that were in the land of Israel; and he appointed stone hewers to hew polished stones to build the house to God. 
\v 3 And David prepared much iron for the nails of the doors and the gates; the hinges also and brass in abundance, there was no weighing \add of it\add*. 
\v 4 And cedar trees without number: for the Sidonians and the Tyrians brought cedar trees in abundance to David. 
\v 5 And David said, My son Solomon \add is\add* a tender child, and the house \add for me\add* to build to the Lord \add is\add* for superior magnificence for a name and for a glory through all the earth: I will make preparation for it. And David prepared abundantly before his death. 
\p
\v 6 And he called Solomon his son, and commanded him to build the house for the Lord God of Israel. 
\v 7 And David said to Solomon, \add My\add* child, it was in my heart to build a house to the name of the Lord God. 
\v 8 But the word of the Lord came to me, saying, Thou hast shed blood abundantly, and hast carried on great wars: thou shalt not build a house to my name, because thou hast shed much blood upon the earth before me. 
\v 9 Behold, a son shall be born to thee, he shall be a man of rest; and I will give him rest from all his enemies round about: for his name \add shall be\add* Solomon, and I will give peace and quietness to Israel in his days. 
\v 10 He shall build a house to my name; and he shall be a son to me, and I will be a father to him; and I will establish the throne of his kingdom in Israel forever. 
\v 11 And now, my son, the Lord shall be with thee, and prosper \add thee\add*; and thou shalt build a house to the Lord thy God, as he spoke concerning thee. 
\v 12 Only may the Lord give thee wisdom and prudence, and strengthen thee over Israel, both to keep and to do the law of the Lord thy God. 
\v 13 Then will he prosper \add thee\add*, if thou take heed to do the commandments and judgments which the Lord commanded Moses for Israel: be courageous and strong; fear not, nor be terrified. 
\p
\v 14 And, behold, I according to my poverty have prepared for the house of the Lord a hundred thousand talents of gold, and a million talents of silver, and brass and iron without measure; for it is abundant; and I have prepared timber and stones; and do thou add to these. 
\v 15 And \add of them that are\add* with thee do thou add to the multitude of workmen; \add let there be\add* artificers and masons, and carpenters, and every skillful \add workman\add* in every work; 
\v 16 in gold and silver, brass and iron, \add of which\add* there is no number. Arise and do, and the Lord \add be\add* with thee. 
\p
\v 17 And David charged all the chief men of Israel to help Solomon his son, \add saying\add*, 
\v 18  \add Is\add* not the Lord with you? and he has given you rest round about, for he has given into your hands the inhabitants of the land; and the land is subdued before the Lord, and before his people. 
\v 19 Now set your hearts and souls to seek after the Lord your God: and rise, and build a sanctuary to your God to carry in the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and the holy vessels of God, into the house that is to be built to the name of the Lord. 
\c 23  
\p
\v 1 And David was old and full of days; and he made Solomon his son king over Israel in his stead. 
\v 2 And he assembled all the chief men of Israel, and the priests, and the Levites. 
\v 3 And the Levites numbered \add themselves\add* from thirty years old and upward; and their number by their polls amounted to thirty and eight thousand men. 
\v 4 Of the overseers over the works of the house of the Lord \add there were\add* twenty-four thousand, and \add there were\add* six thousand scribes and judges; 
\v 5 and four thousand doorkeepers, and four thousand to praise the Lord with instruments which he made to praise the Lord. 
\p
\v 6 And David divided them \add into\add* daily courses, for the sons of Levi, for Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. 
\v 7 And for \add the family of\add* Gershon, Ladan, and Shimei. 
\v 8 The sons of Ladan \add were\add* Jehiel, the chief, and Zetham, and Joel, three. 
\v 9 The sons of Shimei; Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran, three: these \add were\add* the chiefs of the families of Ladan. 
\v 10 And to the sons of Shimei, Jahath, and Zina, and Jeush, and Beriah: these \add were\add* the four sons of Shimei. 
\v 11 And Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second: and Jeush and Beriah did not multiply sons, and they became \add only\add* one reckoning according to the house of their father. 
\p
\v 12 The sons of Kohath; Amram, Izhar, Hebron, Uzziel, four. 
\v 13 The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses: and Aaron was appointed for the consecration of the most holy things, he and his sons forever, to burn incense before the Lord, to minister and bless in his name forever. 
\v 14 And \add as for\add* Moses the man of God, his sons were reckoned to the tribe of Levi. 
\v 15 The sons of Moses; Gershom, and Eliezer. 
\v 16 The sons of Gershom; Shebuel the chief. 
\v 17 And the sons of Eliezer were, Rehabiah the chief: and Eliezer had no other sons; but the sons of Rehabiah were very greatly multiplied. 
\v 18 The sons of Izhar; Shelomith the chief. 
\v 19 The sons of Hebron; Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth. 
\v 20 The sons of Uzziel; Micah the chief, and Isshiah the second. 
\p
\v 21 The sons of Merari; Mahli, and Mushi: the sons of Mahli; Eleazar, and Kish. 
\v 22 And Eleazar died, and he had no sons, but daughters: and the sons of Kish, their brethren, took them. 
\v 23 The sons of Mushi; Mahli, and Eder, and Jeremoth, three. 
\p
\v 24 These \add are\add* the sons of Levi according to the houses of their fathers; chiefs of their families according to their numbering, according to the number of their names, according to their polls, doing the works of service of the house of the Lord, from twenty years old and upward. 
\v 25 For David said, The Lord God of Israel has given rest to his people, and has taken up his abode in Jerusalem forever. 
\v 26 And the Levites bore not the tabernacle, and all the vessels of it for its service. 
\v 27 For by the last words of David was the number of the Levites \add taken\add* from twenty years old and upward. 
\v 28 For he appointed them to wait on Aaron, to minister in the house of the Lord, over the courts, and over the chambers, and over the purification of all the holy things, and over the works of the service of the house of God; 
\v 29 and for the showbread, and for the fine flour of the meat offering, and for the unleavened cakes, and for the fried cake, and for the dough, and for every measure; 
\v 30 and to stand in the morning to praise and give thanks to the Lord, and so in the evening; 
\v 31 and \add to be\add* over all the whole burnt offerings that were offered up to the Lord on the Sabbaths, and at the new moons, and at the feasts, by number, according to the order \add given\add* to them, continually before the Lord. 
\v 32 And they are to keep the charge of the tabernacle of witness, and the charge of the holy place, and the charges of the sons of Aaron their brethren, to minister in the house of the Lord. 
\c 24  
\p
\v 1 And \add they number\add* the sons of Aaron in \add their\add* division, Nadab, and Abihu, and Eleazar, and Ithamar. 
\v 2 And Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and they had no sons: so Eleazar and Ithamar the sons of Aaron ministered as priests. 
\v 3 And David distributed them, even Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, according to their numbering, according to their service, according to the houses of their fathers. 
\p
\v 4 And there were found \add among\add* the sons of Eleazar more chiefs of the mighty ones, than of the sons of Ithamar: and he divided them, sixteen heads of families to the sons of Eleazar, eight according to \add their\add* families to the sons of Ithamar. 
\v 5 And he divided them according to their lots, one with the other; for there were those who had charge of the holy things, and those who had charge of the \add house\add* of the Lord among the sons of Eleazar, and among the sons of Ithamar. 
\p
\v 6 And Shemaiah the son of Nethanel, the scribe, \add of the family\add* of Levi, wrote them down before the king, and the princes, and Zadok the priest, and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar \add were present\add*; and the heads of the families of the priests and the Levites, each of a household \add were assigned\add* one to Eleazar, and one to Ithamar. 
\p
\v 7 And the first lot came out to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah, 
\v 8 the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, 
\v 9 the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin, 
\v 10 the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, 
\v 11 the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah, 
\v 12 the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, 
\v 13 the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, 
\v 14 the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, 
\v 15 the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez, 
\v 16 the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezkel, 
\v 17 the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul, 
\v 18 the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah. 
\p
\v 19 This \add is\add* their numbering according to their service to go into the house of the Lord, according to their appointment by the hand of Aaron their father, as the Lord God of Israel commanded. 
\p
\v 20 And for the sons of Levi that were left, \add even\add* for the sons of Amram, Shubael: for the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah. 
\v 21 For Rehabiah, the chief \add was Izhar\add*, 
\v 22 and for Izhar, Shelomoth: for the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath. 
\v 23 The sons of Ecdiu; Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth. 
\v 24 For the sons of Uzziel, Micah: the sons of Micah; Shamir. 
\v 25 The brother of Micah; Isshiah, the son of Isshiah; Zechariah. 
\v 26 The sons of Merari, Mahli, and Mushi: the sons of Jaaziah, 
\v 27  \add That is, the sons\add* of Merari by Jaaziah—his sons \add were\add* Shoham, and Zaccur, and Ibri. 
\v 28 To Mahli \add were born\add* Eleazar, and Ithamar; and Eleazar died, and had no sons. 
\v 29 For Kish; the sons of Kish; Jerahmeel. 
\v 30 And the sons of Mushi; Mahli, and Eder, and Jerimoth. These \add were\add* the sons of the Levites according to the houses of their families. 
\v 31 And they also received lots as their brethren the sons of Aaron before the king; Zadok also, and Ahimelech, and the chiefs of the families of the priests and of the Levites, principal heads of families, even as their younger brethren. 
\c 25  
\p
\v 1 And King David and the captains of the host appointed to their services the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, prophesiers with harps, and lutes, and cymbals: and their number was according to their polls serving in their ministrations. 
\p
\v 2 The sons of Asaph; Zaccur, Joseph, and Nethaniah, and Asharelah: the sons of Asaph \add were\add* next the king. 
\p
\v 3 To Jeduthun \add were reckoned\add* the sons of Jeduthun, Gedaliah, and Zeri, and Jeshaiah, and Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six after their father Jeduthun, sounding loudly on the harp thanksgiving and praise to the Lord. 
\p
\v 4 To Heman \add were reckoned\add* the sons of Heman, Bukkiah, and Mattaniah, and Uzziel, and Shebuel, and Jerimoth, and Hananiah, and Hanani, and Eliathah, and Giddalti, and Romamti-ezer, and Joshbekashah, and Mallothi, and Hothir, and Mahazioth. 
\v 5 All these \add were\add* the sons of Heman the king’s chief player in the praises of God, to lift up the horn. And God gave to Heman fourteen sons, and three daughters. 
\v 6 All these sang hymns with their father in the house of God, with cymbals, and lutes, and harps, for the service of the house of God, near the king, and Asaph, and Jeduthun, and Heman. 
\p
\v 7 And the number of them after their brethren, those instructed to sing to God, everyone that understood \add singing\add* was two hundred and eighty-eight. 
\p
\v 8 And they also cast lots for the daily courses, for the great and the small \add of them\add*, of the perfect ones and the learners. 
\v 9 And the first lot of his sons and of his brethren came forth to Asaph the son of Joseph, \add namely\add*, Gedaliah: the second Heneia, his sons and his brethren \add being\add* twelve. 
\v 10 The third Zaccur, his sons and his brethren \add were\add* twelve: 
\v 11 the fourth Izri, his sons and his brethren \add were\add* twelve: 
\v 12 the fifth Nathan, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 13 the sixth Bukkiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 14 the seventh Jesharelah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 15 the eighth Jeshaiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 16 the ninth Mattaniah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 17 the tenth Shimei, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 18 the eleventh Azarel, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 19 the twelfth Hashabiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 20 the thirteenth Shubael, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 21 the fourteenth Mattithiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 22 the fifteenth Jeremoth, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 23 the sixteenth Hananiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 24 the seventeenth Joshbekashah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 25 the eighteenth Hanani, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 26 the nineteenth Mallothi, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 27 the twentieth Eliathah, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 28 the twenty-first Hothir, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 29 the twenty-second Giddalti, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 30 the twenty-third Mahazioth, his sons and his brethren, twelve: 
\v 31 the twenty-fourth Romamti-ezer, his sons and his brethren, twelve. 
\c 26  
\p
\v 1 And for the divisions of the gates: the sons of the Korahites \add were\add* Meshelemiah, of the sons of Asaph. 
\v 2 And Meshelemiah’s firstborn son \add was\add* Zechariah, the second Jediael, the third Zebadiah, the fourth Jathniel, 
\v 3 the fifth Elam, the sixth Jehohanan, the seventh Eliehoenai, the eighth Obed-edom. 
\v 4 And to Obed-edom \add there were born\add* sons, Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sachar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth, 
\v 5 Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peullethai the eighth: for God blessed him. 
\v 6 And to Shemaiah his son were born the sons of his firstborn, chiefs over the house of their father, for they were mighty. 
\v 7 The sons of Shemaiah; Othni, and Rephael, and Obed, and Elzabad, and Achiud, mighty men, Elihu, and Semachiah, and Isbacom. 
\v 8 All \add these were\add* of the sons of Obed-edom, they and their sons and their brethren, doing mightily in service: in all sixty-two \add born\add* to Obed-edom. 
\p
\v 9 And Meshelemiah \add had\add* eighteen sons and brethren, mighty men. 
\v 10 And to Hosah of the sons of Merari \add there were born\add* sons, keeping the dominion; though he was not the firstborn, yet his father made him chief of the second division. 
\v 11 Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth: all these \add were\add* the sons and brethren of Hosah, thirteen. 
\p
\v 12 To these \add were assigned\add* the divisions of the gates, to the chiefs of the mighty men the daily courses, even their brethren, to minister in the house of the Lord. 
\v 13 And they cast lots for the small as well as for the great, for the several gates, according to their families. 
\v 14 And the lot of the east gates fell to Shelemiah, and Zechariah: the sons of Soaz cast lots for Melchias, and the lot came out northward. 
\v 15 To Obed-edom \add they gave by lot\add* the south, opposite the house of Esephim. 
\v 16  \add They gave the lot\add* for the second to Hosah westward, after the gate of the chamber by the ascent, watch against watch. 
\v 17 Eastward \add were\add* six \add watchmen\add* in the day; northward four by the day; southward four by the day; and two at the Esephim, 
\v 18 to relieve guard, also for Hosah westward after the chamber gate, three. \add There was\add* a ward over against the ward of the ascent eastward, six \add men\add* in a day, and four for the north, and four for the south, and at the Esephim two to relieve guard, and four by the west, and two to relieve guard at the pathway. 
\v 19 These \add are\add* the divisions of the porters for the sons of Korah, and to the sons of Merari. 
\p
\v 20 And the Levites their brethren \add were\add* over the treasures of the house of the Lord, and over the treasures of the hallowed things. 
\v 21 These \add were\add* the sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonite: to Ladan \add belonged\add* the heads of the families: \add the son\add* of Ladan the Gershonite \add was\add* Jehieli. 
\v 22 The sons of Jehieli \add were\add* Zetham, and Joel; brethren \add who were\add* over the treasures of the house of the Lord. 
\v 23 To Amram and Izhar belonged Hebron, and Uzziel. 
\v 24 And Shebuel the \add son\add* of Gershom, the \add son\add* of Moses, \add was\add* over the treasures. 
\v 25 And Rehabiah \add was\add* son to his brother Eliezer, and \add so was\add* Jeshaiah, and Joram, and Zichri, and Shelomoth. 
\v 26 This Shelomoth and his brethren \add were\add* over all the sacred treasures, which David the king and the heads of families consecrated, \add and\add* the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, and princes of the host, 
\v 27 things which he took out of cities and from the spoils, and consecrated some of them, so that the building of the house of God should not want \add supplies\add*; 
\v 28 and over all the holy things of God dedicated by Samuel the prophet, and Saul the son of Kish, and Abner the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Zeruiah, whatsoever they sanctified \add was\add* by the hand of Shelomoth and his brethren. 
\p
\v 29 For the Izharites, Chenaniah, and \add his\add* sons \add were over\add* the outward ministration over Israel, to record and to judge. 
\v 30 For the Hebronites, Hashabiah and his brethren, a thousand and seven hundred mighty men, \add were\add* over the charge of Israel beyond Jordan westward, for all the service of the Lord and work of the king. 
\v 31 Of the \add family\add* of Hebron Jerijah \add was\add* chief, even of the Hebronites according to their generations, according to their families. In the fortieth year of his reign they were numbered, and there were found mighty men among them in Jazer of Gilead. 
\v 32 And his brethren \add were\add* two thousand seven hundred mighty men, chiefs of their families, and King David set them over the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, for every ordinance of the Lord, and business of the king. 
\c 27  
\p
\v 1 Now the sons of Israel according to their number, heads of families, captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, and scribes ministering to the king, and for every affair of the king according to \add their\add* divisions, \add for\add* every ordinance of coming in and going out monthly, for all the months of the year, one division of them \add was\add* twenty-four thousand. 
\p
\v 2 And over the first division of the first month \add was\add* Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel: in his division \add were\add* twenty-four thousand. 
\v 3 Of the sons of Perez \add one\add* was chief of all the captains of the host for the first month. 
\v 4 And over the division of the second month \add was\add* Dodai the son of Ahoh, and over his division \add was\add* Makelloth also chief: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand, chief men of the host. 
\v 5 The third for the third month \add was\add* Benaiah the son of Jehoiada the chief priest: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 6 This Benaiah \add was\add* more mighty than the thirty, and over the thirty: and Ammizabad his son \add was\add* over his division. 
\v 7 The fourth for the fourth month \add was\add* Asahel the brother of Joab, and Zebadiah his son, and his brethren: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 8 The fifth chief for the fifth month \add was\add* Shamhuth the Izrahite: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 9 The sixth for the sixth month \add was\add* Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 10 The seventh for the seventh month \add was\add* Helez of Pelon of the children of Ephraim: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 11 The eighth for the eighth month \add was\add* Sibbecai the Hushathite, \add belonging\add* to Zerah: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 12 The ninth for the ninth month \add was\add* Abiezer of Anathoth, of the land of Benjamin: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 13 The tenth for the tenth month \add was\add* Maharai the Netophathite, \add belonging\add* to Zerah: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 14 The eleventh for the eleventh month \add was\add* Benaiah of Pirathon, of the sons of Ephraim: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\v 15 The twelfth for the twelfth month \add was\add* Heldai the Netophathite, \add belonging\add* to Othniel: and in his division \add were\add* twenty and four thousand. 
\p
\v 16 And over the tribes of Israel, the chief for Reuben \add was\add* Eliezer the son of Zichri: for Simeon, Shephatiah the son of Maacah: 
\v 17 for Levi, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel: for Aaron, Zadok: 
\v 18 for Judah, Elihu of the brethren of David: for Issachar, Omri the son of Michael: 
\v 19 for Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah: for Naphtali, Jeremoth the son of Azriel: 
\v 20 for Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Azaziah: for the half-tribe of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah: 
\v 21 for the half-tribe of Manasseh in the land of Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah, for the sons of Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner: 
\v 22 for Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham: these \add are\add* the chiefs of the tribes of Israel. 
\p
\v 23 But David took not their number from twenty years old and under: because the Lord said that he would multiply Israel as the stars of the heaven. 
\v 24 And Joab the son of Zeruiah began to number the people, and did not finish the work, for there was hereupon wrath on Israel; and the number was not recorded in the book of the chronicles of King David. 
\p
\v 25 And over the king’s treasures \add was\add* Azmaveth the son of Adiel; and over the treasures in the country, and in the towns, and in the villages, and in the towers, \add was\add* Jonathan the son of Uzziah. 
\v 26 And over the husbandmen who tilled the ground \add was\add* Ezri the son of Chelub. 
\v 27 And over the fields \add was\add* Shimei of Ramah; and over the treasures of wine in the fields \add was\add* Zabdi the son of Shiphmi. 
\v 28 And over the olive yards, and over the sycamores in the plain country \add was\add* Baal-hanan the Gederite; and over the stores of oil \add was\add* Joash. 
\v 29 And over the oxen pasturing in Sharon \add was\add* Shitrai the Sharonite; and over the oxen in the valleys \add was\add* Shaphat the son of Adlai. 
\v 30 And over the camels \add was\add* Obil the Ishmaelite; and over the asses \add was\add* Jehdeiah of Meronoth. 
\v 31 And over the sheep \add was\add* Jaziz the Hagrite. All these \add were\add* superintendents of the substance of King David. 
\p
\v 32 And Jonathan, David’s uncle by the father’s side, \add was\add* a counselor, a wise man: and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni \add was\add* with the king’s sons. 
\v 33 Ahithophel \add was\add* the king’s counselor: and Hushai the chief friend of the king. 
\v 34 And after this Ahithophel Jehoiada the son of Benaiah \add came\add* next, and Abiathar: and Joab \add was\add* the king’s commander-in-chief. 
\c 28  
\p
\v 1 And David assembled all the chief \add men\add* of Israel, the chief of the judges, and all the chief \add men\add* of the courses \add of attendance\add* on the person of the king, and the captains of thousands and hundreds, and the treasurers, and the lords of his substance, and of all the king’s property, and of his sons, together with the eunuchs, and the mighty men, and the warriors of the army, at Jerusalem. 
\p
\v 2 And David stood in the midst of the assembly, and said, Hear me, my brethren, and my people: it was in my heart to build a house of rest for the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and a place for the feet of our Lord, and I prepared \add materials\add* suitable for the building: 
\v 3 but God said, Thou shalt not build me a house to call my name upon it, for thou art a man of war, and hast shed blood. 
\v 4 Yet the Lord God of Israel chose me out of the whole house of my father to be king over Israel forever; and he chose Judah as the kingly \add house\add*, and out of the house of Judah \add he chose\add* the house of my father; and among the sons of my father he preferred me, that I should be king over all Israel. 
\v 5 And of all my sons (for the Lord has given me many sons), he has chosen Solomon my son, to set him on the throne of the kingdom of the Lord over Israel. 
\v 6 And God said to me, Solomon thy son shall build my house and my court: for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be to him a father. 
\v 7 And I will establish his kingdom forever, if he continue to keep my commandments, and my judgments, as \add at\add* this day. 
\v 8 And now \add I charge you\add* before the whole assembly of the Lord, and in the audience of our God, keep and seek all the commandments of the Lord our God, that ye may inherit the good land, and leave it for your sons to inherit after you forever. 
\p
\v 9 And now, \add my\add* son Solomon, know the God of thy fathers, and serve him with a perfect heart and willing soul: for the Lord searches all hearts, and knows every thought: if thou seek him, he will be found of thee; but if thou shouldest forsake him, he will forsake thee forever. 
\v 10 See now, for the Lord has chosen thee to build him a house for a sanctuary, be strong and do \add it\add*. 
\p
\v 11 And David gave Solomon his son the plan of the temple, and its buildings, and its treasuries, and its upper chambers, and the inner storerooms, and the place of the atonement, 
\v 12 and the plan which he had in his mind of the courts of the house of the Lord, and of all the chambers round about, \add designed\add* for the treasuries of the house of God, and of the treasuries of the holy things, and of the chambers for resting: 
\v 13 and \add the plan\add* of the courses of the priests and Levites, for all the work of the service of the house of the Lord, and of the stores of vessels for ministration of the service of the house of the Lord. 
\v 14 And \add he gave him\add* the account of their weight, both of gold and silver \add vessels\add*. 
\v 15 He gave him the weight of the candlesticks, and of the lamps. 
\v 16 He gave him likewise the weight of the tables of showbread, of each table of gold, and likewise of the \add tables of\add* silver: 
\v 17 also of the fleshhooks, and vessels for drink offering, and golden bowls: and the weight of the gold and silver \add articles\add*, and censers, \add and\add* bowls, according to the weight of each. 
\v 18 And he showed him the weight \add of the utensils\add* of the altar of incense, \add which was\add* of pure gold, and the plan of the chariot of the cherubs that spread out their wings, and overshadowed the ark of the covenant of the Lord. 
\v 19 David gave all to Solomon in the Lord’s handwriting, according to the knowledge given him of the work of the pattern. 
\p
\v 20 And David said to Solomon his son, Be strong, and play the man, and do: fear not, neither be terrified; for the Lord my God \add is\add* with thee; he will not forsake thee, and will not fail thee, until thou hast finished all the work of the service of the house of the Lord. And behold the pattern of the temple, even his house, and its treasury, and the upper chambers, and the inner storerooms, and the place of propitiation, and the plan of the house of the Lord. 
\v 21 And see, \add here are\add* the courses of the priests and Levites for all the service of the house of the Lord, and \add there shall be\add* with thee \add men\add* for every workmanship, and everyone of ready skill in every art: also the chief men and all the people, \add ready\add* for all thy commands. 
\c 29  
\p
\v 1 And David the king said to all the congregation, Solomon my son, whom the Lord has chosen, \add is\add* young and tender, and the work \add is\add* great; for \add it is\add* not for man, but for the Lord God. 
\v 2 I have prepared according to all \add my\add* might for the house of my God gold, silver, brass, iron, wood, onyx stones, and costly and variegated stones for setting, and every precious stone, and much parian \add marble\add*. 
\v 3 And still farther, because I took pleasure in the house of my God, I have gold and silver which I have procured for myself, and, behold, I have given them to the house of my God over and above, beyond what I have prepared for the holy house. 
\v 4 Three thousand talents of gold of Ophir, and seven thousand talents of fine silver, for the overlaying of the walls of the sanctuary: 
\v 5  \add for thee to use\add* the gold for \add things of\add* gold, and the silver for things of silver, and for every work by the hand of the artificers. And who is willing to dedicate himself in work this day for the Lord? 
\p
\v 6 Then the heads of families, and the princes of the children of Israel, and the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, and the overseers of the works, and the king’s builders, offered willingly. 
\v 7 And they gave for the works of the house of the Lord five thousand talents of gold, and ten thousand gold \add pieces\add*, and ten thousand talents of silver, and eighteen thousand talents of brass, and a hundred thousand talents of iron. 
\v 8 And they who had \add precious\add* stone, gave it into the treasuries of the house of the Lord by the hand of Jehiel the Gershonite. 
\v 9 And the people rejoiced because of the willingness, for they offered willingly to the Lord with a full heart: and King David rejoiced greatly. 
\p
\v 10 And King David blessed the Lord before the congregation, saying, 
\p Blessed art thou, O Lord God of Israel, our Father, from everlasting and to everlasting. 
\v 11 Thine, O Lord, \add is\add* the greatness, and the power, and the glory, and the victory, and the might: for thou art Lord of all things that are in heaven and upon the earth: before thy face every king and nation is troubled. 
\v 12 From thee \add come\add* wealth and glory: thou, O Lord, rulest over all, the Lord of all dominion, and in thy hand \add is\add* strength and rule; and \add thou art\add* almighty with thy hand to increase and establish all things. 
\v 13 And now, Lord, we give thanks to thee, and praise thy glorious name. 
\v 14 But who am I, and what \add is\add* my people, that we have been able to be thus forward \add in offering\add* to thee? for all things \add are\add* thine, and of thine own have we given thee, 
\v 15 for we are strangers before thee, and sojourners, as all our fathers \add were\add*: our days upon the earth \add are\add* as a shadow, and there is no remaining. 
\v 16 O Lord our God, as for all this abundance which I have prepared that a house should be built to thy holy name, it is of thy hand, and all \add is\add* thine. 
\v 17 And I know, Lord, that thou art he that searches the hearts, and thou lovest righteousness. I have willingly offered all these things in simplicity of heart; and now I have seen with joy thy people here present, willingly offering to thee. 
\v 18 O Lord God of Abraham, and Isaac, and Israel, our fathers, preserve these things in the thought of the heart of thy people forever, and direct their hearts to thee. 
\v 19 And to Solomon my son give a good heart, to perform thy commandments, and \add to observe\add* thy testimonies, and thine ordinances, and to accomplish the building of thy house. 
\p
\v 20 And David said to the whole congregation, Bless ye the Lord our God. And all the congregation blessed the Lord God of their fathers, and they bowed the knee and worshiped the Lord, and \add did obeisance\add* to the king. 
\v 21 And David sacrificed to the Lord, and offered up whole burnt offerings to the Lord on the morrow after the first day, a thousand calves, a thousand rams, a thousand lambs, and their drink offerings, and sacrifices in abundance for all Israel. 
\v 22 And they ate and drank joyfully that day before the Lord: and they made Solomon the son of David king a second time, and anointed him king before the Lord, and Zadok to the priesthood. 
\p
\v 23 And Solomon sat upon the throne of his father David, and was highly honored; and all Israel obeyed him. 
\v 24 The princes, and the mighty men, and all the sons of King David his father, were subject to him. 
\v 25 And the Lord magnified Solomon over all Israel, and gave him royal glory, such as was not upon any king before him. 
\p
\v 26 And David the son of Jesse reigned over Israel forty years; 
\v 27 seven years in Hebron, and thirty-three years in Jerusalem. 
\v 28 And he died in a good old age, full of days, in wealth, and glory: and Solomon his son reigned in his stead. 
\v 29 And the rest of the acts of David, the former and the latter, are written in the history of Samuel the seer, and in the history of Nathan the prophet, and in the history of Gad the seer, 
\v 30 concerning all his reign, and his power, and the times which went over him, and over Israel, and over all the kingdoms of the earth. 